title: 15 inch MacBook Pro retina (i7, 16gb, 512gb) dual graphics
description:
I'm selling my beloved 15 inch MacBook Pro with retina display, 16 GB of RAM, and 512 GB solid-state hard drive space. 
 
macOS Sierra 
Version 10.12.2 
 
Processor: 2.3 GHz Intel core i7 
Memory: 16 GB 1600 MHz DDR3 
Graphics: Dual 
    -Nvidia GeForce GT 750M 2048 MB 
    -Intel iris Pro 1536 MB 
 
I find it important to understand why someone is selling; below are my reasons: 
 
This is my absolute favorite laptop and was perfect for my first two years of medical school. I am no longer in the classroom and I am constantly on the go. I am unable to fit a 15 inch computer in my whitecoat pocket; as a father, I hardly have an opportunity to 'sit'. I hope to pass on this wonderful device to someone who will appreciate it as much as I do and will benifit from it more than I can.  
 
I proudly say it isn't free of any blemishes as this laptop is too useful to keep in a closet untouched. There is one small indentation in the middle of the right speaker grille, peraps the laptops most vulnerable location to a falling frigerator magnet (couresey of my 2-year old son). The back right external corner also shows wear (multitidue of times entering and exiting my bag). 
 
This is the very last Macbook Pro Retina prior to apple implementing the force touch trackpad. If you are familiar with apple products over the past 10 years, you already notice the absence of Steve Jobs. My Macbook Pro is his last design . My machine has an ethereal charm that is missing on the new force touch models. Perhaps it's sentimental, but see for yourself if you wish.

title: 1992 s10 pro street or trade for???
description:
1992 gmc Sonoma/ chevy s10 up for sale, it's a project that needs minimal work to get roadworthy. I just don't have the time or will to finish it now. So offering it up for sale to see what happens. Not desperate to sell it either, I know what it's worth and won't let it go too cheap. It's a super clean pro street build with a daily driver in mind. All orignal Equipment in the truck works fine ac, heater, wipers,lights...exct 
 
Mods list 
 
Pro street rear end,  
ford 9 HD axle housing 
moser 31 spline billet axles 
Detroit tru trac posi 
3.75 Richmond gears 
willwood 4 piston disc brake setup with internal parking brake 
locar parking brake cables (not yet installed) 
inland empire custom HD driveshaft 
moroso billet u-joint griddles 
insane innovations made the traction bars with hiem joints for the rear end 
qa1 rear coilover kit with 150lb springs in the rear 
belltech 2' front drop kit (springs,shocks and drop spindals) 
new balljoints, tie rods, and all front steering coponents 
built 700r4/4l65 trans, 5 pinion planatarys,  
shift kit 
2800rpm pro torque converter 
be-cool aluminum radiator setup with fans, aluminum overflow, and electric thermostat (currently not installed, have the OEM cooling system in the truck) 
built 4.3 v6, comp cam, new heads, TBI setup..was planning on a sequential rear mounted turbo setup that would defenently brake into the 600 horsepower range 
custom billet grille, front bumper and front spoiler with extensions that wrap around the fenders 
street scene mirrors (heated mirror with signals)  
custom tail lghts 
fiberglass rear roll pan 
zo6 chrome 18' wheels with brand new 295/35/18 tires (only have a pair) 
interior is in great condition,  
Camaro bucket seats (some tears, not bad) 
autometer 3 gauge pod 
autometer c2 trans temp gauge 
autometer c2 oil temp gauge 
autometer c2 air fuel ratio gauge 
tilt steering collum  
 
That's all I can think of off the top of my head, there is defenently more parts to the list. I will have to sort through the recepts. 
 
now for the bad- The truck is not done. It needs a little work to run/drive under its own power.   
Fuel- Need to install and plumb the gas tank. Was planning on running a custom 14 gallon fuel cell but im loosing intrest in the project 
Brakes- rear brake lines need to be plumbed as well. Need a hardline to a T, that branches out to each caliper.  
Suspension- Need a custom panhard bar. Summit sells a kit for the 9' housing for about 120 bucks.  
 
Im loosing intrest in the project due to my work schedule. I thought id have time to finish the truck before summer hit but the way things are looking currently it would have to wait till next year. I work in the HVAC industry and we are currently builsy. Don't have the time to finish it. and really don't want to pay a shop to finish something that I can do. So I thought id throw it out for sale and see if I get any offers. I may also be interested in a trade. Im looking for a fullsize truck. Suburban 4x4,Classic chevy trucks, or something like a Silverado single cab short bed, or a dually... those would be at the top of my list. but shoot me any offer for trade. worst I can say is no! thank you for reading!

title: Comic Books - All are now $1 each
description:
***All comics are now $1 and you can pick and choose. These didn't sell as a lot but they need to go so come get a handful for $1 each.*** 
 
I am selling off my entire comic book collection. There are a little over 520 books total. The collection is mainly Marvel but there is also some DC, Image, etc.  
 
Marvel titles include Deadpool, Spider-Man, X-Men and spin-offs (Wolverine, Gambit, etc), Avengers and spin-offs (Iron Man, Captain America, Hulk, Hawkeye, etc). There are soooooo many more. 
 
The DC books are mostly Batman, some Harley Quinn, and some others. 
 
For Image there are a few Walking Dead books, Outcast, Chew and some random others. 
 
There are some TV show adaption books too.... Angel, Orphan Black, Mortal Kombat, Jay and Silent Bob and more. 
 
There are horror books... zombies and such. 
 
A handful of older books in there too... from 70's and 80's 
 
There are quite a few collectible books in there too! There are some small runs and key issues mixed in there. 
 
[$2 Books] There are some magazines and a couple graphic novels as well. I have a bunch of signed books too. Original TMNT books signed by Kevin Eastman with COA. There are some TMNT magazines also signed and numbered by Eastman also with COA and a few other Image books signed by authors at comic shows. These are worth a lot more than this but they need to go so they are all being sold for $2 each. 
 
All books are in great and collectible condition. I bought a bunch of them from a store that went out of business so they were flipped through and some do have some spine stress but nothing major. Just about all of them range from VF+ to NM or NM-. Of course there are some older books that are lower than that. I'm not a pro grader.

title: 2003 Custom Pro Street Motorcycle
description:
VETTE CULTURE  
MESA, ARIZONA  
 
 
480-807-8000 
 
 
 
2003 Custom Pro Street motorcycle (Built in 2003, first registered in 2004). Fantastic bike! 
 
* Pro Street chassis by Deliverance Cycles 
* Bike built by Unique Cycle Creations 
* 6 speed Baker transmission 
* HD Evolution 1340 motor with mid-range performance cam 
* Dual Weber side draft carbs 
* Pro One brake calipers 
* Custom paint by "Bad Ass" out of Los Angeles 
* Dakota Digital display 
* Inverted forks with brand new seals 
* Rear tire 230/60/15 
* Arlen Ness headlight 
* 13,648 original miles 
* Excellent condition 
* Have build pictures and build details 
 
 
 
VETTE CULTURE FINANCING AVAILABLE ON ALL CARS WITH VERY COMPETITIVE RATES WITH TERMS UP TO 84 MONTHS. SIGN AND DRIVE.   
Please visit us at WWW.VETTECULTURE.NET  to view our additional inventory! 
 
Hablamos Espanol! 
Por favor si tiene alguna pregunta contactenos. 
 
All of our vehicles go through our extensive Vette Culture inspection prior to sale at our Performance/Service Center (see below for details). Comprehensive "bumper to bumper" Extended Warranties are available for all of our stock or custom built/modified Corvettes. 
 
*FOR THE COMPLETE VETTE CULTURE EXPERIENCE, PLEASE CALL AHEAD TO SCHEDULE A VIEWING APPOINTMENT. 
*Please serious inquires only. 
*Please contact us with questions by phone. 
 
 
Corvette Super Retail/Performance Center: 
As a specialty Corvette Center we operate a professional, comfortable, no pressure environment for our clients.  Because we show our cars by appointment only we can and do take the time to know our clients' needs - saving you time and money.  Vette Culture is Owner operated, which means you are working directly with a decision maker that has a long term interest in your satisfaction. 
Our Corvette retail/service facility is a Corvette enthusiast's paradise. Our inventory is stored indoors within our 12,000 square foot showroom and is available for viewing by appointment only. 
For our out-of-town clients, we are conveniently located within a 20 minute drive east of Phoenix-Sky Harbor International Airport (PHX) and directly adjacent to Falcon Field Airport (FFZ) for those clients arriving by private aviation.  We are happy to offer our clients complimentary ground transportation between the airports and our facility. 
At Vette Culture, we are here to make purchasing your vehicle as easy as possible. We can coordinate shipping with one of several licensed and bonded transportation companies to deliver your vehicle direct to your door.  Costs will vary depending upon the desired level of service (for example, open carrier vs. enclosed carrier). 
 
All of our vehicles go through our extensive Vette Culture inspection prior to sale at our Performance/Service Center. 
 
The Vette Culture comprehensive inspection includes (very broadly): 
 
-Paintwork and trim condition (searching for crash damage, new paint and poor workmanship, established corrosion). For the early cars this would include a more detailed body (fiberglass) check. 
-Underbody and suspension condition. 
-Wheels and tire condition. 
-Operation of brakes and brake disc/pad condition. 
-The engine and transmission external condition (oil leaks, coolant and consumables condition, corrosion). 
-The interior and rear hatch compartment (wear and tear leather/carpet). 
-Operation of electrical equipment. 
-Basic document check (original equipment/service book/Navigation discs). 
-Experian car data/background check. 
-GM VIN verification and in service records (covers original equipment ordered/bulletins and recalls/in service date and build date verification). 
-On the C5/C6/C7 models, including the 1997-onwards OBD ECM/PCM cars, we use GM Tech 2 diagnostic equipment to analyze and diagnose all ECM/PCM data (faulty censor/diagnostic codes and history checks). 
 
At the Vette Culture Performance Center we offer pre-engineered packages and complete design-build services for your custom Corvette project. Covering all Parts, Accessories, and Performance needs for the C2/C3/C4/C5/C6/C7 Corvette. 
Our Performance Center capabilities include:    
-Custom paint and body. 
-Custom interiors (high grade leather/suede hides). 
-Custom wheels and tires/Powder Coating/Chrome/Paint. 
-Custom one of a kind fabricated products/modifications. 
-Headers and Exhaust systems/one of a kind custom built exhaust systems. 
-Superchargers. 
-Performance Cam packages for the LS1/LS2/LS3/LS6/LS7/LS9/LT1/LT4 and more. 
-Performance Engine building/ECM Precise Performance Tuning. 
-Suspension adjustments/lowering/coil overs. 
-Brakes/Caliper/Rotor packages. 
-Vette Culture brand products made specifically for your Corvette. 
-Comprehensive Extended Warranties for stock or modified Corvettes. 
 
Our Service Center capabilities include: 
-ONE STOP SHOP-We can do it all at the Vette Culture Performance Center. 
-Vette Culture is a certified GM Tech 2 and HP Performance Tune Center. 
-I-CAR Certified. 
-Routine maintenance. 
-Corvette diagnosis and repair experts. 
-Warranty service work. 
- Minor and major performance modifications. 
-Cosmetic transformations/restoration. 
-Wheel and tire packages at very competitive prices. 
 
TERMS OF SALE: 
Vette Culture makes no representations, expressed or implied, to any actual or prospective purchaser or owner of this vehicle as to the existence, ownership, accuracy, description or condition of the listed vehicle's equipment, accessories, price, specials or any warranties. Any and all differences must be addressed prior to the sale of this vehicle. 
 
Advertised prices exclude License, Title, Registration Fees, State or Local Taxes or Delivery Fees/dealer document fee. The dealer document fee is $399.00 and will be added to the final sales price. 
 
PROPER VENUE: All obligations pursuant to this contract shall be performable in Maricopa County, in the state of Arizona. All obligations of purchaser to pay for the vehicle shall be payable in U.S. dollars in Maricopa County, Arizona. The buyer and Vette Culture agree that in relation to any transaction involving this vehicle that the proper venue for any legal proceedings will be conducted in Maricopa County, Arizona. 
DO NOT contact me with unsolicited services or offers

title: Massive 85L Backpack LOADED with BRAND NEW Camping Gear & Daypacks!!!
description:
Massive 85L Backpack LOADED with BRAND NEW Camping Gear & Daypacks!!!  
 
> > > IS SPRING IS RIGHT AROUND THE CORNER? NO! IT'S HERE NOW!! < < < 
 
> > > FIRST COME, FIRST SERVED < < < > > > FIRST COME, FIRST SERVED < < < 
 
$ $ $ $ $ - - 1 OF 3, SOLD! ONLY 2 LEFT, NOW!! - - $ $ $ $ $  
 
* * * NOTE * * *  
Whereas I am firm on the pricing of the three "large pack bundles" and the remaining "daypack bundles," my intent in selling these items is not only to recoup a (very) FEW bucks, but to also get rid of the inventory. Therefore, those who buy the already low-priced LARGE pack and Daypack bundles, I am more than willing to throw in a few extras of your choice -- and/or negotiate an even lower price on the extra item/s (provided they're still available). 
 
For the purpose of full disclosure, over the years, I have sampled/tested several different brands and models of backpacks, in return for honest feedback regarding their functionality, size, weight and comfort, etc. Though I've never been paid to do this, I was obviously allowed to keep the backpacks regardless of the feedback. One of the companies was Outdoor Products (OP), though it "was not" the particular daypack I'm offering below. I've never sampled or accepted anything from Alps Mountaineering. Over three years ago, I chose the two backpacks offered below based solely upon their versatility, exceptional construction, price and 101 other reasons -- all based upon my first-hand experience in the field with them.  
 
Also see my listing for 12 expertly hand-painted, camouflaged 5-Gal Buckets and GAMMA SEAL Lids! 
http://phoenix.craigslist.org/cph/for/
  
html 
 
Greetings! 
 
A Little History: 
I am finally getting around to selling the remaining inventory I have from my little start-up business, "The Dual-Survival Backpack," from several years ago. In 2012/13, I had the great idea of offering to the public, a backpack that was fully and completely equipped to go off the grid for between 3-6 days. The idea, I thought (and still do!!), was to have the well-equipped backpack available for people who were looking for a very solid pack -- be they beginning or experienced hikers -- either for just getting away for a few days for a fun-filled time with Mother Nature, or in the event of some kind of disaster/civil unrest/act of terrorism, etc., as a bugout bag.  
 
After I sold several, I suffered two major back-to-back, untreated concussions, while . . . you guessed . . . hiking. Being propelled by a rock hidden in the tall grass, and falling forehead-first on a ground level boulder, just ain't good for ya! The first concussion of the "two in five days," actually caused the second fall and concussion. 
 
Anyhoo, due to the lingering effects of those two concussions (and others, prior:), I found I no longer had what it took to run the business, and kind of closed up shop. Today, I still have some inventory left over that I would finally like to get rid of AT VERY LOW PRICES!! Every single item has been tested backwards and forwards, and I stand by everything to be the best you can buy for the money. And that's NOT to say that any element of these packs are cheaply made; they're NOT!  
 
I don't have all the items that went into the original DSBP pack -- yet I'm not charging the original selling price of $1,100, either. However, the meat-and-potatoes are still in there. No food items are included in these packs.  
 
EVERY ITEM OFFERED IS BRAND NEW! It "may" (and I mean MAY) have been used in a photo shoot or two, but never used! Each LARGE pack (see below); Brand New! * Sleeping bags; Brand New! * Day packs; Brand New! * Stoves; Brand New! * Sleeping bag mats; Brand New! *** ALL of the other items? BRAND NEW! *** Still, everything sold "as is" because of maybe a blemish or two on it??? But everything sold is in 110% working condition! 
  
$ $ $ $ $ - - 1 of 3 LARGE PACKS ALREADY SOLD! ONLY 2 LEFT, NOW!! - - $ $ $ $ $  
 
As I said, I am selling the items in as many "bundles" as I can, thus I've broken down the sale three ways: 
 
1)	LARGE Packs -- $350. ea. (see below) include all the items shown in the photos of that particular bundle. If you're just starting out, or you have a friend who needs a very well stocked, LARGE, long-haul backpack, you can't beat this for price and quality -- guaranteed!!! Were you thinking about trekking a LONG, multi-WEEK trail in one of our beautiful National Parks soon? This is your answer!! 
 
I spent literally weeks-at-a-time testing every part included it in my DSBP packs, making sure that those items that made the final cut, were up to a standard of quality that I was happy to stand behind. Everything that made up my DSBP packs was tested in every temperature and element Arizona has to offer, including four-days in a miserable wet snow storm in Flagstaff, several October days/nights in Utah and horrendous monsoon season thunderstorms, with all the high winds and downpours they can offer and temperatures as high as 105-degrees, during the summer. To this day, dollar-for-dollar, I would change only one or two things about it; THAT'S IT! 
  
2)	Daypacks -- $35. ea. is a STEAL! Do your research . . . I have 10 additional Daypacks that I am selling, and including for FREE, my own, personally made Wilderness First-Aid Kit, a $45. value! This homemade Kit has everything you need, and nothing you don't, for heading off-trail or hiking. As long as supplies last, I'm happy to throw in extras -- also at no additional charge -- such as bug spray, etc., and sell other items, if you're interested, at discounted prices (AS LONG AS SUPPLIES LAST). 
 
3)	Remaining additional items sold singly, or in quantities (WHILE SUPPLIES LAST, Ssee below): 
_______________________________________________________ 
 
List of Items Bundled With LARGE Pack (ONLY! $350. ea):  
- - 1 of 3 LARGE PACKS ALREADY SOLD! ONLY 2 LEFT, NOW!! - - 
 
*  Alps Mountaineering, Cascade 5200 (See the first two photos and list below for included items) 
This is the best, simplest, most well constructed large -- or small -- backpack I've ever owned, and I've own/owned many backpacks! I've had my personal Cascade 5200 for over five years now, and have logged-in well over a thousand miles with this pack on my back (usually weighing in at least 45-50 lbs. fully loaded, with two, full, 3L hydration packs inside). With only three of these left, you might think I'd keep one for myself, but I'm not. My Cascade 5200 shows no signs of giving up -- even in the next five years!  
 
The capacity of this monster is 5200 cubic-inches, 85-liters. To give you an idea of its size, you can place a 2L bottle of soda in each SIDE pocket, with room to spare. The included fanny pack (which can also be used as a pack "topper"), could probably hold two, 2L bottles of soda, but it certainly holds one with much room to spare (See photos). Not that I condone carrying around 2L bottles of soda, just using them as a visual. 
  
More info can be found via the following link. Keep in mind my packs are "olive green," and although they are brand new and unused, they do have a little patch of my company logo affixed to the front, as I used them in photo shoots.

title: ******  LIFTED F150 SUPER CREW LARIAT !!!  ******
description:
One of a kind truck!  Lariat Edition, 5.4 liter V8 engine, 4 door, pearl white paint, all leather, power everything, back up camera, back up sensors, full screen stereo with navigation and voice controls, tinted windows, differential re-geared to same ratio as new Raptors, over sized differential cover, true cold air intake by Volant, programmer, magnaflow exhaust upgrade, 6" pro comp lift, Newer Toyo Open Country A/T tires, BMF black and machined wheels, AMP automatic running boards with LED lights, remote start alarm.....  I am probably missing something, I have done too much!  Actually, yes....I have installed a black grill and black fender flares since I took these pictures.  I will update pictures later today.  I don't race the truck or go off road, I am just a car enthusiast, since I am in the automotive business.  Your truck should look good, sound good, and be able to accelerate when needed!   
 
Truck has 120k miles, which isn't much these days.  I run a auto repair shop, so all repairs done when with Ford OE parts only, no aftermarket crap.  All oil changes performed with Mobil 1 Synthetic with premium filters.  I can only imagine the anxiety of looking for a used vehicle, especially since most people are cheap and don't fix their vehicles when they should or use Auto Zone junk parts.   Cant tell you how many people don't fix their vehicles, because they are going to get rid of it!  Don't be the guy that buys someone else's problems!   If you are looking for a truck that has been professionally maintained, is in perfect condition, and already has all the bells and whistles, this is your truck!  I encourage you to drive it and have it inspected by your own shop!  Truck is in new condition, mechanically, inside and out!   
 
I am the second owner, my co-worker was the original owner.  I am a non smoker.

Chevrolet Performance developed these ZZ4 crate engines, which are evolved from the popular ZZ series of small blocks that power thousands of street rods, hot streetcars, circle track racers and drag racers. These ZZ4 350 c.i.d., 4-bolt main, 1-piece rear main seal crate engines have approximately 10.0:1 compression, 355 hp at 5,250 rpm and 405 ft./lbs. of torque at 3,500 rpm. To make this package work Chevrolet Performance has installed forged 1053 steel internally balanced crankshafts, 5.7 in. powdered metal connecting rods with hypereutectic flat top pistons with offset pins. title: 1996 GMS Drums - 6 piece drum set - RARE AND AMAZING!!!
description:
This is a USA made GMS 6 piece drum set that I am selling.  It is a great looking and awesome sounding versatile kit!  With 4 toms you can really adjust to the style and genre of music you want to play. 
 
I am willing to sell with or without hardware - it all needs to go. 
 
GMS Drums are a boutique drum manufacturer from NY and make some amazing drums!  http://gmsdrums.com/ This is a kit built in 1996 that features maple shells with a white lacquer finish.  (see photo with stamp, they are all stamped but I didn't photo each one) 
1996 was the year they introduced their proprietary suspension mounting system as is featured on these drums. 
These are without a doubt some of the best sounding drums I've had the chance to own 
 
Specs: 
24" Bass 
10", 12", 13", 16" Toms 
14"x6" Snare - matching maple 
 
Tom heads are within a year old, never gigged with them and are Evans 360 2-ply heads, nice versatile sound, with a good balance of attack and resonance.  Snare has a Remo Controlled Sound coated head.  Drum kick head is an Evan Emad 2 with dampening ring (don't know the age) and the bass resonant head is the original with the GMS logo, the previous owner had put a piece of tape on a tear, doesn't affect the sound too much that I can tell but doesn't look the best either.    
 
The hardware is a bit of a mixed bag including Gibraltar hi hat (also a ludwig hi hat stand) (2) DW double braced boom/straight combo cymbal stands and a Tama single braced boom/straight combo cymbal stand, also a DW 5000 double chain single bass pedal.  There are a few misc. hardware pieces that I can include as welL. 
 
Cymbals: 
14" hi hat including ZHT Mastersound on top and Zildjian Aveidas on bottom. 
18" A Custom Zildjian Crash 
20" Sabian El Sabor Ride  
14" Sabian B8 Crash 
  
These drums are 21 years old and are in really great, but not perfect shape; however dollar for dollar these rival or top the likes or similar drum company's high end line of drums. There's not many of these being sold around the country, look around and you will see. 
I am open to offers, contact me to discuss more.  Thanks

title: Lenovo X1 Carbon Ultrabook Notebook - i7 / 8gb RAM / 256 SSD *EXTRAS*
description:
I write code for a living.   
 
What I am offering for sale is a total computing solution rather than a mere computer.  I bought it as a graduation present to myself for $1200 a couple years ago it was incredibly fast then and even faster now. 
 
The lenovo x1 carbon is pretty much the perfect amount of machine.  It masterfully blends power and performance while not cutting many corners.  Here are the raw specs, they kind of tell most of the story: 
 
Lenovo X1 Carbon, weighs 2 lbs 15 oz (see picture) 
 
Intel i5 2.5ghz multi core processor Hyper-Threading Technology, Intel Turbo Boost Technology 2.0 3mb cache, integrated memory controller 
 
8GB 1333 MHz PC3-10600 Ram 
 
120 GB Solid State Disk Drive 
 
Intel HD Graphics 4000 
 
Full size spill-resistant backlit keyboard 
 
Buttonless touchpad (like a macbook pro) 
 
Bluetooth 4.0, Ethernet, Fast Ethernet, Gigabit Ethernet 
 
Mini DisplayPort, USB 2.0, USB 3.0, headphone/microphone combo jack 
 
Fingerprint Scanner 
 
and all this is encased in a durable and impossibly light carbon fiber, magnesium-aluminum alloy frame. 
 
This machine cost $1500 in 2012 and it's easy to see why. 
 
 
If i had any complaints about this machine then it was merely  too few output ports.  Fret not, I got you covered, remember when I said total computing solution? 
 
So I am including with this machine - A docking station/port replicator that will send outputs to three different displays (that's a lotta desktop) as well as add an additional. 
 
When you plug this dock into the lenovo you will instantly add the following ports to the Carbon X1 
 
2 x USB 3.0 -- 1 provides always-on mobile device charging 
2 x USB 2.0 
1 x DVI-D 
1x Gigabit Ethernet 
1x Stereo/Mic Combo Port 
 
So in other words, you can leave a wireless mouse, wireless keyboard, a larger external display, a printer, and an external DVD drive plugged in to the stationary dock, and when you get home, plug the dock into your carbon and your home office springs to life.   
 
It's a pretty damn cool setup.  My price may seem high, but there's a reason for that.  I've done all the work for you, and am including several accessories.  this is ready to go. 
 
THIS WILL ALSO COME WITH A FULLY ACTIVATED COPY OF MS OFFICE 2016 PROFESSIONAL PLUS & PHOTOSHOP CS6 PREINSTALLED ON THE COMPUTER.

title: Gasser Fiberglass from www.CalAutomotiveFiberglass.com
description:
Hello, We are now offering authentic "vintage" Race Car & Hot Rod fiberglass bodies and parts. While we are a new company, our roots are very much in the past. Most of our molds are from some of the oldest companies in the business & were used to create some very famous cars!  Like our  '32 Austin Bantam ("Pure Hell") - Fiat Topolino ("Magic Muffler", "Milodon", "Mondello & Matsubara") 2 versions of the "Marcellus & Borsch" 23 T, "Deuce" roadster,  27 T roadster, 23 T "Tub" & 2 other T "Buckets" all original "Fiberglass by Cal Automotive" molds..... our  Austin A-40 sedan and pickup are the original "Contemporary Fiberglass" molds.... We have '40-'41 Willys components and a '23 T with 1 opening door from Jim Kirby's "Challenger Components" molds.      
 Others are molds that were made from some very famous cars, like our chopped 33 Willys, pulled from the original 'Brasher & Cummings' Gasser by "Pacific Fiberglass" in 1980.... All were made by some of the oldest "fiberglass hands" in the business...  
 We also have about 50 part numbers in our "Scoops & Spoilers" section that are original "A&A Fiberglass" molds. These range from the early Gasser & Super Stock stuff thru the "Dyno Don" & "Sox & Martin" Pro Stock up to some of the early 90's Aero stuff... Also Corvette, Camaro & Mustang "Muscle Car' scoops like the L-88. Z-L1, Z-28, Cobra Jet, etc.  Rear Spoilers for '67 - '81 Camaro, Universal & a few 1990's "Aero" style. 
 Are you building a "period correct" vintage race car or Hot Rod? What could be more correct than Hand Laid Fiberglass from molds with this history? We are going thru great lengths to restore each and every one of our molds. Our aim is to deliver to you the EXACT SAME PART that you would have bought way back then... To that end we are working closely with some of the "founding fathers" of this industry....  
 Check out our selection of fiberglass dashes... like the "Cal Automotive" / "Magoo" Model "A" dash.... 
 We also have '58 & '63 Corvette Go-kart bodies - Austin A-40 "roadster" pedal car/go kart (copied from the original factory pedal car!) - '41 Willys coupe and pickup "mini" Go-kart (35" wheelbase) - 41 willys coupe, 32 Ford & Austin A-40  baby stroller bodies!  
 The website, www.calautomotivefiberglass.com is up and running, not complete but we hope to be soon...  
 We are working on a printed catalog, right now we do have a rough draft in .PDF format that we will email out to anyone that asks for it.... 
 
            SEE OUR ADS ON RACING JUNK !! 
 
"Ken's Cal Automotive Fiberglass" wants to be your Authentic Vintage Fiberglass Source! 
Thank You

title: Jeep Wrangler JK Lift, Tires, Wheels and Heavy Duty Tire Carrier
description:
URBAN KRAWLER PACKAGE!! 
 
- Are you looking for the best combination of parts that allows your Jeep Wrangler JK to be both a comfortable daily driver as well as a capable weekend off-road rig? 
 
- Is it confusing trying to pick out all of the lift components you want or need - what height should you go, what size tire can you fit, will you need to re-gear the axles?? 
 
- Do you hate shops that don't listen to your needs, that don't explain exactly what you're buying or that try to sell you parts that are more of a benefit to them than you? 
 
- What brand is best - do you choose AEV, TeraFlex, Rubicon Express, Rock Krawler, Pro Comp or Rough Country?? 
 
- Do you want to trust your expensive Jeep to a shop that actually drives Jeeps themselves and has been building Jeeps since 2001, including Jeeps for major automotive aftermarket manufacturers like TeraFlex, Bushwacker, Truck-Lite/Rigid Industries, Rugged Ridge, BOLT Lock, Grizzly Coolers and Rhino Linings to name just a few? 
 
If you answered yes to any of these questions, then Doetsch Off-Road is your solution! We only deal with Jeep Wranglers and are THE best at what we do. Our showroom is stocked full of Jeep Wrangler parts & accessories and is affectionately called the "Jeep Candy Store"! 
 
For a limited time, we're offering stage 1 of our most popular Jeep Wrangler JK build package, called the "Urban Krawler", at a special price of only $5,000 OUT THE DOOR - that's all parts, supplies, labor, tax, alignment, tire/wheel mount & balance plus transfer of your OEM tire pressure monitoring sensors (TPMS), lug nuts, heavy duty spare tire carrier....EVERYTHING IS INCLUDED!! 
 
Here's what you get in the Urban Krawler Stage 1 package: 
 
**SUSPENSION** 
- A TeraFlex 2.5" Suspension lift with shocks, which is an ultra simple performance oriented lift kit that provides amazing highway drivability with very capable off road performance. Drivability and performance are the most important factors that are engineered and built into every TeraFlex lift kit. Properly developed suspension geometry, roll center, and load tuning ensure that all factory stability controls remain functional and within the parameters that Jeep originally engineered into the vehicle. TeraFlex kits drive straight and will crawl anything, getting you there and back! This kit includes 2.5" lift coil springs, 9550 VSS shock absorbers, rear swaybar links, heavy duty rear trackbar axle bracket, bumpstop extensions and all necessary hardware.  
**You can also upgrade to our Stage 2 package which includes a 3" TeraFlex lift, front adjustable monster trackbar and control arm drop brackets, by simply paying the difference. We also offer shock upgrades to brands like Bilstein or Fox!* 
 
**TIRES** 
- Five 35x12.50R18 (295/70R18) Nitto Trail Grappler tires (includes a matching spare tire) which are road and trail proven. Just Google this tire and read the reviews from other Jeep owners! For off-road performance, the 3-ply sidewall and thick rubber construction increase puncture resistance. On the tread surface, the blocks provide additional biting edges that command lateral stability and enhance forward traction. For on-road comfort, Nitto's engineers used advanced sound analysis equipment to systematically reduce noise levels commonly associated with off-road tires for a quieter drive. 
 
**WHEELS** 
- Your choice of any five (spare included) matching 18x9/18x10 KMC, XD Series or ATX Series Wheels that we have in stock....like the XD126 Enduro Pro, XD127 Bully, XD128 Machete, XD798 Addict, XD807 Strike, XD811 RS2 or AX195 Cornice! 
 
**LUG NUTS** 
- You probably don't want your original nasty chrome lug nuts to clash with your brand new wheels, so we included a complete black splined lug nut kit that features a total of 23 lugs and a spline key - that's enough to outfit all four tires plus your spare! 
 
**HEAVY DUTY TIRE CARRIER** 
- Don't try to run an oversized tire on the wimpy factory tire carrier and there's also no need to replace your rear bumper just yet just so you can have an aftermarket swing away tire carrier - we include the Rugged Ridge Spartacus HD Tire Carrier System and it also allows you to keep your OEM 3rd brake light. This kit provides the ultimate in strength and stability for mounting your oversized wheel and tire. Functionally designed to manage the amplified force and vibrations produced during extreme off-road conditions. The precision die-cast aluminum Hinge Casting provides maximum strength without the excess weight of steel. The one-piece design maintains one-handed access to cargo area and rigidly links the Wheel Mount to the reinforced section of the rear quarter panel. This, in combination with forged steel hinge brackets and hardened steel pins, results in far superior load capacity than the factory tailgate hinges, thereby effectively reducing wear and increasing longevity. The Wheel Mount lifts the mounting position and incorporates depth and tilt adjustability for large diameter and wide tire options. Tested to MIL-STD-810 to simulate extended duration of vigorous off-road driving conditions. Rated for up to and including 37" wheel tire combinations. Includes adjustable third brake light bracket. Compatible with OE and most aftermarket rear bumpers. No drilling required. 
 
**ALL LABOR, FEES & TAXES** 
- All the labor to install the lift, perform a professional 4-wheel alignment after the lift is installed, mount & balance your five wheels & tires PLUS move over your original Tire Pressure Sensors (TPMS) to the new wheels/tires and the labor to install the Rugged Ridge HD tire carrier system. 
 
So that's everything you need to start the build of a capable off-road trail Jeep while still keeping the on road handling that you may be used to. We also offer additional package accessories like steel aftermarket front AND rear bumpers for $350 (front or rear), Power Dome style hoods for $399, front or rear catch-all rubber floor mats for $60, LED cube lights starting at $100 for a pair plus a whole lot more!! We can easily add anything yo want to the package. 
 
The package components listed above apply to any 2007, 2008, 2009, 2010, 2011, 2012, 2013, 2014, 2015, 2016 r 2017 Jeep Wrangler JK or JKU Unlimited regardless if it is a Sport, Sahara, Rubicon, Hard Rock, Willys Edition, Polar Edition, 10th Anniversary Rubicon, Rubicon X, Black Bear Edition, etc. We also offer separate CJ, YJ and TJ packages so just call us for details! 
 
Pics show some examples of the Urban Krawler Stage 1 package installed on various Jeeps, some of which have other optional accessories installed such as flat style fender flares, aftermarket bumpers from brands like JCR Offroad / Poison Spyder / Smittybilt / Rock Hard / Rampage and more!, LED lighting, roof racks, exhaust systems and more! All of which we also sell and can bundle into the package for even more savings!!

title: 2013 Axis A22
description:
ONLY 13 HOURS, in pristine condition, always kept covered in a temperature controlled garage. 
Custom trailer with Rock Star Wheels. 
Loaded with options. Featuring: Monsoon 330, wake board tower w/speakers, board racks, tower mirror, Bimini top, ballasts, Wedge, full instrumentation, cruise, tilt steering, Sony AM/FM CD USB satellite ready stereo w/amp and sub, flip-up bolster driver's seat, snap out carpet, cup holders, tons of storage, dual batteries w/switch, full boat cover, and a tandem axle trailer w/matching spare and folding tongue.  
2013 Axis A22 All Systems GO When it's time to look and feel good on the water, the A22 is your wing-man.  
At 22 feet, the Axis A22 is the perfect size for creating a massive wake and comfortably fitting 14 of your friends while still maintaining maneuverability and ease of trailering. Wakes are clean and reliable with just the right pop at every level from factory ballast all the way up to pro levels with added weight. Wake surfing is just as easy on the A22 with a giant swell that has a long pocket and plenty of power. Inside this wake-centric 22-footer, Axis made a clean, sharp interior with an emphasis on function displayed in the twin-tip bow and the wraparound lounge seating. The FatAX tower perfectly coincides with the A22's industrial look, and the easy-to-use speed control makes for perfect pulls every time. 
The Axis A22 is the best boat for you if: You want a midsize, stylish wake boat that's all about the rider. The A22's wake performance is good enough for riders like Randall Harris and Dean Smith, so it ought to be more than sufficient for you and your friends. 
Girls like it, guys dig it and families share their best moments with it. Loads of improvements have been made for 2013, including HI FLO ballast pumps and hoses, which decrease your fill and drain time dramatically. This also helps for quick weight adjustments on the fly. A panoramic mirror gives the driver a 140-degree view, so the rider always is in frame. Optional GPS speed control delivers a smooth pull, so riders can focus on landing new tricks with no worries. Updates include an improved driver-side dash system, with Wedge position indicator and auto volume control, automotive style, three-vent heater system in the dash and foot well. The new vinyl, which is grained for comfort and durability, and creates a plush look and feel. 
For more information, please call

title: 2010 Polaris RZRS 800 HO Factory FOX long travel!
description:
Why spend 25k on a new one when you can spend less than half that and have just as much fun? 9xx miles, less than 1000 miles! Nearly new! 
 
New battery. 
Lots of tread left on tires. 
Todd's Custom Billet Aluminum  roll cage with Spare tire rack (not currently on back but takes 5mins to install) and padded doors, almost $3k alone new. This is beefier than stock roll cage and all tubing is 1/2" thicker. 
All engine is stock with exception of Dobecks Gen4 Air to Fuel ratio gauge that keeps engine from running too lean or rich, optimizes power using O2 sensor welded into stock exhaust bung. Can be returned to stock easily in 5 mins if desired. 
Washable KandN air filter with pre-filter. 
4 point seat harnesses with sternum strap and camlock that releases all points with a flick of the wrist. 
Half windshield, best way to go. Don't even need goggles to keep the wind out of your eyes and you can see right over it when it gets dusty. 
Snorkel kit, but I never used it, it was the previous owner's thing but works if desired. Has extended breather tubes for everything to shoulder height. 
Aluminum Billet shifter from Mod Squad.

title: 2011 Suzuki M109R Limited Edition
description:
Well, It wasn't easy, but I've made a tough decision - I'm giving up my beautiful motorcycle to focus more time and resources on my brand new muscle car... i know, i know, first-world problems, right?! 
 
This is the ever-menacing and head-turning 2011 Suzuki Boulevard M109R Limited Edition in eye-catching Black and Orange. Nothing else on the road looks quite like the M109R - I can't count the head nods and thumbs-up this thing has gotten over the years. I've added a Cobra 2-into-1 Pro Tip exhaust with the Fi2000 ECU - she screams like a banshee on the throttle and snarls like a hellcat on roll-off. And the acceleration and performance are night-and-day from the stock package! I also added a couple of smaller custom touches - some sharp-looking grips and tear-drop mirrors to maximum the "black-out" effect. 
 
The bike has been garage-kept since day one and I'm a fair-weather rider, so it only has 4,400 miles on it and has NEVER been on its side. The single-seat cowl and passenger seat are both included and can be easily swapped out in two minutes with an allen wrench. 
 
I hate to see it go, but I know I'm not riding it like it needs to be ridden. I've got the clear title in-hand, so give 'er a good home and GIVE 'ER HELL!

title: 1949 Chevy/ GMC pickup
description:
1949 GMC 3100 pickup truck. The truck is titled as a GMC, but it does have a Chevy front end on it. I have over 100 photos of the ground up build of my truck. This is a serious restoration/ modification build in which every single nut, bolt, wire, line, etc has been touched. Every inch of the truck is detailed.  
5.7 LS engine dynoed at 325 hp at the wheels. Power adders include Comp camshaft, Pro Products intake manifold, K&N intake system, 3" mandrel bent and tig welded exhaust, stainless headers, Frontrunner serpentine belt system, etc. The transmission is a 4l60e and was brand new from B&M. The rear end is a GM 12 bolt, rebuilt with new gears, bearings, seals, and limited slip.  
Chassis has G body suspension up front from Ridetech with adjustable coilovers with both height adjustment and dampening adjustments. The rear suspension is a custom built, fully adjustable, parallel 4 link with panhard bar and adjustable Ridetech coilovers. The big brake package has 13" rotors all the way around and a CPP master cylinder and booster setup. The truck rolls on 20"x8.5" (front) and 20"x10" (rear) Intro billet wheels wrapped in 245/40r20 and 275/49r20 Toyo Proxes ST ii tires. All the suspension has been powder coated gloss black, the chassis and the rest of the components have been painted. The exhaust is ceramic coated from the headers all the way to the rear bumper.  
The exterior of the truck has been cleaned up of all rust and a few custom touches have been added, but it still retains a mostly stock appearance. It is painted a pearl white found on the newer Cadillacs. The under side of the 4 fenders, the engine compartment, the interior, and every where but the underside of the cab are all painted in the same manor as the parts you see. The underside of the cab, the cab floor, the inside of the firewall, under dash, and inside back wall of the cab have all been seam sealed, sealed, and bedlined. The bedfloor is oak and has been stained and clear coated.  
The interior is very comfortable for an old single cab truck. The dash has been treated to Dakota VHX gauges, new chrome dash trim with Hydrodipped inserts to match the bedfloor. The seat frame is original, but all the springs were removed in favor of all new webbing and foam for a much more comfortable seat. The door panels, kick panels, and center console are all custom built and everything has been wrapped in a leather like material. The stereo system includes a pioneer double din touch screen DVD unit, two sets of 6" component speakers, two 10" subs, and one 5 channel amplifier ... all from Rockford Fosgate. The truck also has a Vintage Air Gen ii AC system.  
The truck was an inside booth vehicle at Sema 2015 for the company that supplied me with the paint materials for the truck. It was the focus of several tech articles in Street Trucks magazine. It made the cover of Street Trucks magazine in 2016 as well. It also was featured in an episode of Auto Revolution.  
I'm sure I'm missing some details, but I think you'll get the idea from that. If you have any questions, feel free to ask. I've put over 1,100 miles on the truck since it's been "done." So, please don't think it's only a trailer queen. Because of the fact that I've driven it, it's not 100% perfect. However, it's darn close... especially the main parts of what you see. You won't be able to go anywhere without compliments! 
Price is an asking price. Feel free to negotiate. I'm open to offers. I am not open to trades though. I have a 3 year old and another son due next month. So I just don't have the need for the truck now, or anytime in the near future.

title: 2004 Subaru WRX Rally (EJ207)
description:
I have here an immaculate Subaru WRX 2.0 L Turbo. Very clean!!! No leaks. No accidents no rebuilt title. Car was purchased by my father stock in 2013 (I bought it from him last year). It has since been heavily upgraded. Engine was swapped at 157,000 miles, the new engine (EJ207) was Imported from Japan. Currently running stock map on it, but it does come with a Cobb tuner with 3 maps. I've only put a couple thousand since the swap several months ago. The car is has been babied and been well taken care of. Really don't want to get rid of it but life happens. I'm in no hurry to sell it just testing the market, a lot of money has been put into my baby. You won't find another Subaru like it!! List of upgrades below: 
 
Engine Upgrades 
-Rebuilt engine in 2014 with stock oem Subaru EJ205 parts and oem Subaru gasket kit. 
-Swapped engine in 2016 with JDM EJ207 with AVCS (Shipped from Japan) 
-Big 16G Turbo (T-05E) 
-STI Up pipe

-Red Perrin 3" upgrade induction hose (inlet to turbo) w/ air inlet pipe fittings

-All new oem Subaru fluids replaced and overhaul 
-Installed new power steering pump and 0-rings 
-Charged A/C system up (ice cold) 
-Replaced battery 
 
 
Suspension and Brakes 
-Installed new STI WRX front Brembo drilled brake rotors and Brembo STI 4 piston calipers with brembo pads on front and rear of car 
-Stainless Steel Brake Lines (Brand new, just did these) 
-Cobb Shifter Bushing upgrade

-Rear Strut Bar 
-2007 Forester KYB GR-2 Struts 
-06 STI Front Control Arms

Body

-Rally Armor Mud Flaps 
-All Weather Floor Mats 
-Front bumper air splitters

-Full custom built Gorilla (out of Chicago) front push bar with 4000 lb winch mount on front

-1 Cree 28" led flood/spot light bar mounted on roof-rack with relay and blue genesis toggle switch on dash

Interior

-Front & Rear Boston Acoustics 4 channel amp (475gt) with 4 Boston pro 6.5 component speakers and cross-overs

-All doors and floors lined with dynomat for sound deadening

Extra 
-Car was tuned at Dynocomp (2014) with 3 maps: 18psi, 16psi, 10psi plus your stock economy map. Dyno sheets are included for all three maps. 
-Cobb Accessport Tuner. Currently in stock mode, was at 18psi producing 310hp with the older engine, haven't dyno'ed it yet on the new engine but I'm sure it's pushing more around 360 hp when running at 18psi or higher. 
-Comes with log book of every detail that has been done to the car.

KBB value is $? @ 12,138 new miles (new engine, but not including upgrades) 
It has over 8K in upgrades!!! Around 20K spent on this car. 
 
Of course no one ever gets what they put into cars so I'm entertaining offers, let me know what you think. Price is negotiable but this is not a STOCK SUBARU!!! title: Native Machine Groove Studio
description:
This is brand new never used in open box. Comes with software. Purchased for $999 at Sweetwater. Sacrificing for $775 obo.  
 
Native Instruments 
See all items from Native Instruments 
Product Description 
With a vast sound library, intuitive controls and visual feedback like never before, the Native Instruments Maschine Studio Groove Production Studio is the flagship beat-maker from NI! Two high-res color screens show waveforms, patterns, scenes, and mixer and meter levels in full detail. Multi-color pads provide ultimate feel in the thick of the beat. Maschine Studio's pattern-based sequencer and high-performance sampler, exemplary drum synths, suite of effects and instruments deliver ultimate power.  
Maschine Studo Silver 
 
 
The included Maschine 2.0 delivers a spectacular, tag-based visual browser, unlimited groups and insert effects, sidechaining, and a sleek, intuitive mixer -- all directly accessible from the Maschine Studio. Maschine 2.0 hosts any VST or AU plug-in and perfectly integrates into any studio setup as a plug-in in all major DAWs. The software also boasts full multi-core support for ultra-fast performance.  
 
Native Instruments Maschine Studio Groove Production Studio Features 
Two hi-resolution color screens for the fastest, most intuitive workflow for creative, computer-based beat production 
Highly-sensitive, multi-color pads provide ultimate feel in the thick of the beat 
Loaded with a vast 8 GB sound library 
Included are 8627 samples including 445 full drum kits, 388 multi-sampled instruments, 403 sliced loops, 1200 patterns, and 38 projects 
Five sonically-outstanding drum synths let you dial in an infinite range of custom sound from ultra-realistic acoustic hits to the hardest hitting electronic drums 
Includes MASCHINE 2.0 software, instruments, and new drum synths 
24 pro-quality studio effects 
Dedicated edit buttons and an ultra-precise jog-wheel let you browse, edit, and arrange faster than you ever thought possible 
Hi-res color displays allow you to browse plug-ins, edit waveforms to arranging and mixing 
The left screen gives you a full overview of the sample or slice 
The right screen shows the section you're editing in detail 
Parameter knobs directly under the displays let you tweak straight from the hardware 
Always shows you the full pattern or scene in the left display. The right display follows recorded events with precision 
Polish your tracks to perfection with Maschine 2.0's audio mixer 
All-new Maschine 2.0 software features improved browsing, arranging, and sampling for the most responsive, fluid, and musical beatmaking experience ever 
Machine 2.0 mixer and plug-in strip deliver a new paradigm in instant visibility 
Sonically-outstanding drum synths and powerful effects let you design production-ready sounds with ultimate ease 
Enjoy ultra-tight integration with KOMPLETE 9 instruments and effects 
Full versions of MASSIVE, PRISM, SCARBEE MARK I, and SOLID BUS COMP are already on-board 
Browsing 
Maschine Studio's ultra-fast browsing gives your creativity no time to slow down. Do all your browsing directly on Maschine Studio's two high-res color screens -- any project, group, sound, instrument, effect or sample at your fingertips without ever thinking about the computer.  
 
Find your sounds fast with Maschine 2.0's tag-based attribute browser. Load KOMPLETE Instruments and Effects with ultra-clear product icon views from Maschine Studio'S screens. And when you're head-deep in sound design, Maschine lets you tag your own sounds and samples for lightning-fast retrieval later -- fast, complete immersion in your personal sound world.  
 
The Mixer 
Polish your tracks to perfection with the pro audio mixer in Maschine 2.0. Tweak volume, pan, solo or mute with ultimate ease. See group and individual track levels clearly on meters complete with peak level indicators. Adjust levels on any group of sounds with one knob -- simply select the desired channels, then turn the knob under the displays to adjust.  
 
Maschine 2.0 delivers a new paradigm in signal routing. Unlimited sound groups let you manage even the most demanding projects. Two aux sends per channel let you freely route sounds anywhere in your project. Send them to a simple effect or route them to multiple effect chains across several channels. Best of all, you see plug-ins and insert effects directly on the hardware.  
 
Arranging 
16 ultra-sensitive pads deliver classic groovebox feel with tons of power on tap. Get full velocity control, pad link, advanced note repeat, plus swing controls for sounds, groups, and the global project. Color-code your sounds and see your entire sonic palette at a glance.  
 
A clip-based pattern sequencer with full visual feedback means your ideas come together fast. See the full pattern in Maschine's left display while the right display follows your work with precision detail. Edit patterns, nudge notes, change velocity, and more with 8 display knobs, dedicated edit buttons, and Maschine Studio's jog wheel without ever looking at a computer screen.  
 
Sample 
Native Instruments Maschine Studio's two high-resolution color displays give you all you need for ultra-accurate sampling. The left screen always gives you a full overview of the sample you're editing. The right screen shows you the detailed view. Parameter knobs directly under the waveform mean you never break your editing focus by having to look at the computer.  
 
Sample any source no matter the size -- length and number of samples are only limited by your computer's RAM. Get up to 64 voice polyphony for each sound, plus choke, legato, and glide control. Vintage MPC 60 and SP1200 sampling modes deliver the feel of classic drum machines with all the advantages of modern software. And new 8-point sample interpolation is twice as accurate as MASCHINE 1, delivering incredible sample quality.  
 
Slice 
Slice your samples with laser-like precision. Find the flavor that fits you best with four different modes: 
Detect Mode detects your sample's transients and creates slices based on sensitivity settings. With automatic zero-point detection, MASCHINE 2.0 positions markers at the point where the sound wave crosses the zero axis so every slice is pop- and click-free. 
Grid Mode slices your samples according to grid divisions you select. The slices are then cut on the grid itself. 
Split Mode slices the sample into equal parts. Select from 4, 8, 16 or 32 slices per sample. 
Manual Mode lets you add slices anywhere in the sample. Set any amount of slice markers per sample -- great for easily adding slice markers to an entire song and not just a defined region. 
Maschine makes it easy to demo your slices by automatically assigning each slice to one of Maschine Studio's 16 high-sensitivity pads. Quickly cycle through them and make adjustments on the fly on 8 display knobs.  
 
Edit 
Import REX2 and MPC sample formats or import your personal sample library. Maschine Studio handles it all easily. Get creative with a full toolbox of destructive editing features including truncate, normalize, reverse, cut, copy, paste, fade-in, fade-out, silence, DC correct, and duplicate. Maschine's acclaimed offline timestretching and pitchbending with automatic beat detection deliver unrivaled sample quality.  
 
Drum Synth 
Create your own electronic and acoustic drum sounds in truly peerless sound quality. Five monophonic drum plug-ins built exclusively for Maschine 2.0, each with several unique algorithms give you any percussive sound you need. All fully tweakable, automatable from the hardware, and perfectly integrated into Maschine Studio -- with the quality that comes from NI's acclaimed DSP expertise.  
 
Kick Plug-In 
Each of the kick plug-in's eight sound engines delivers unique, powerful low end. Three engines are based on classic analog machines made famous over thirty years of electronic music. They deliver sounds fat and punchy to deep and dusty, and everything in between.  
 
Snare Plug-In 
The snare plug-in features nine different sound engines. Create any imaginable electronic snare -- the snare plug-in does thin, harsh, bold, deep, and filtered with equal ease. Acoustic-like sounds are the sonic wonders of this plug-in -- recreate not only the sound of real snare drums, but also completely change their character and tuning with the turn of a knob.  
 
Hi-Hat Plug-In 
Get classic analog hi-hats, digital, robotic sounds from a complex oscillator, or ultra-modern synthesis from Fast Fourier Transform data of analyzed and reconstructed hi-hat samples. This data gives you ultra-powerful synthesis without having to use samples at any stage of sound production. And quick tweaks deliver other percussion possibilities outside the range of simple hi-hat sounds for endless versatility.  
 
Tom Plug-In 
Three tom engines let you intuitively craft a full set of toms fast. Digital sounds from percussive to bell-like to completely alien. And acoustic sounds so warm and fat you won't believe they're not samples. Added control over pitch bend and mute parameters give you a flexible set of sounds that are ultra-intuitive to create.  
 
Percussion Plug-In 
The percussion plug-in features three sound engines and a world of possibility. Design any additional percussion your project needs from bell-like and metallic to sub-like and twisted with one engine. A second engine is dedicated to shaker and maraca sounds. The third is capable of rich, orchestral timpani sounds ready to add big symphonic percussion to any production.  
 
Instruments Included 
Maschine Studio comes with four full-version KOMPLETE Instruments and Effects, worth over $400 in total. Each KOMPLETE Instrument is perfectly integrated into the Native Instruments Maschine Studio environment, with presets browsable from the hardware and tweakable via the eight display knobs -- automatically mapped to that instrument's parameters.  
 
MASSIVE (synthesizer)  
The star of the Maschine library -- the legendary synthesizer for devastating bass and leads. MASSIVE gives you a total of over 1,300 sounds, all crafted by leading artists and sound designers. Hear it in action  
 
REAKTOR PRISM (synthesizer)  
A highly playable instrument and effects processor. Perfect for organic soundscapes, percussive keys, flutes, bells, basses and shimmering leads. 370 ready-to-play sounds and 50 FX presets. Hear it in action  
 
SCARBEE MARK I (electric piano)  
The legendary electric piano of the 1970s, sampled to perfection in all its analog brilliance. Ranges from warm and mellow to bright and 'barking', and can also produce chiming bell-like tones. Hear it in action  
 
SOLID BUS COMP (effect)  
The perfect tool to glue drum groups or entire mixes together. Powerful, transparent compression for any task -- complete with Dry/Wet control and side-chain input. Hear it in action  
 
Ready to Go Effects 
Get 23 high-quality effects for instant sound enhancement. Classic and Feedback Compressor, Tape and Tube Saturators, a transient designer, reverbs, filters and EQs plus highly creative tools such as Grain-Delay, Ice Verb, Freq Shifter, and more are ready for action.

title: TRAXXAS SLASH 1/10 2WD ELECTRIC SHORT COURSE TRUCK 58034-1
description:
The award-winning Traxxas Slash Short-Course Race Truck puts you in the drivers seat for intense fender-to-fender, high-flying off-road action. The full-scale Short-Course Race Trucks embody the spirit of Traxxas R/C with their extreme 900+ horsepower racing engines full-throttle, dirt-roosting power slides, giant suspension travel, and Supercross-style big-air jumps. The Traxxas Slash brings all the action home so you can experience the high-speed head-to-head competition at the track or in your own backyard. The Slash was inspired by the TORC™ (THE Traxxas Off-Road Championship™) Pro 2WD class. The Pro 2WD class specifies rear-wheel drive trucks purpose built to fly over jumps and rip full-throttle through the turns. The Traxxas Slash hangs it out for an all new way to challenge your driving skills. The 4-wheel independent suspension has been carefully tuned to replicate the Pro 2 driving and handling experience as closely as possible. The scale appearing tires provide just the right amount of bite and thick, blinding clouds of dirt roost. When the racing action cools down, the Traxxas Slash is well-equipped to tackle all of your off-track driving adventures. The long travel suspension and oil-filled shocks easily absorb jumps and rough terrain. The unique chassis design provides huge center ground clearance to drive over deep ruts, rocks, and other obstacles that leave ordinary R/C trucks stuck. The tires use advanced tread design and sophisticated rubber compounds to provide incredible grip off-road with enough versatility to also perform well on concrete and asphalt. The fenders cover the tires so you bang against your driving buddies without getting tangled up. The Revo-spec Torque-Control™ slipper clutch design delivers smooth operation, precise adjustment, and consistent traction control. The bellcrank steering system virtually eliminates bump steer for precise handling and control. A digital steering servo delivers lightning fast response. Traxxas shocked enthusiasts with the release of our exclusive watertight, sealed electronics in the E-Maxx that provided the freedom to drive where you want to drive through water, mud, snow, and other wet-running conditions that wouldn't have been possible before. The proven XL-5 electronic speed control and the mini receiver are sealed against the elements giving you the freedom go places you might not have thought possible. It opens up a whole new world of adventure and fun. Wet muddy tracks are no problem for the Slash. The battery compartment makes it easy to install batteries and the clever design makes it quickly adaptable for either 6 or 7-cell running (hump packs or stick packs).The Titan 12T 550 modified motor is designed for incredible mod-motor power output with virtually maintenance-free operation, and long-lasting performance. The Titan 12T 550 motor's integrated cooling fan pulls cool air through the motor to keep temperatures down. Airflow is routed through vent tunnels molded in the motor plate. A cooler running motor equates to faster speeds, longer runtime, and extended motor life. The XL-5 Electronic Speed Control offers high current handling, EZ-Set® one-button setup, and smooth high-frequency control. Three drive profiles, low voltage detection, thermal shutdown protection, gold-plated connectors, and incredibly low resistance are all features you might expect to only be available on an expensive replacement ESC. As today's batteries store more and more energy inside their cells, traditional battery connectors could no longer keep up. The included patented Traxxas High-Current Connector opens the door for unrestricted current flow. With the TQ™ 2.4GHz radio system, you just switch on a drive. There are no channels or frequencies to manage, so the focus is on having fun. The TQ's ergonomic design is comfortable for all-day driving, and its sleek lines are enhanced by an internal antenna that is impervious to damage. Traxxas' exclusive patented Training Mode let's everyone get in on the racing action. Just press a button to limit full-throttle power to 50%. This allows young or new drivers to safely develop their control skills before unlocking full power to the mighty Titan 12T motor. The Slash is perfect for drivers at all experience levels. Training mode even makes it easy to hand the transmitter over to your friends who have never driven a radio controlled truck before. The Traxxas Slash model 58034 comes fully-assembled and Ready-To-Race® with the TQ radio system installed and adjusted, XL-5 power system, Power Cell 7-cell NiHM battery, wall charger, a painted and decaled body, pre-glued tires, and detailed instructions. There's a reason this powerful RC machine is a classic. Add it to your RC arsenal today. 
 
Fully assembled and ready to race! 
Precision TQ 2.4 GHz Radio Control System 
Water-proof electronics to survive races in all the elements. 
Titan 12 Turn 550 Modified Motor for maintenance free, maximum power. 
XL-5 Waterproof Electronic Speed Control 
New advanced 4-amp DC Peak Detecting Fast Charger

title: 2001 Dodge Ram Lifted
description:
Are you tired of driving around in some un-American compact job? Are you tired of all of those pesky obstacles when you drive, such as parking curbs, priuses, and the occasional mountain? Are you over not being able to see into other peoples' cars and snoop in their business? Then I have the vehicle for you. 
This bad boy is is lifted 2001 Dodge Ram 1500, and will get you wherever you need to go, as long as there is a gas station nearby. I bought this fine rig a few years ago with 88k on the odometer and haven't been able to keep my wrenches away from in since I brought it home. See below for the benefits of owning this fine piece of pure American baddassery.  
 
The Truck is a 2001 Dodge Ram 1500 Laramie Edition, equipped with A/C, power locks and windows, and the fire breathing, liberal roasting 5.9l V8 Magnum. It runs and drives just fine around the city and will cruise at 75 down the highway. The biggest issue I have with the truck is the the commie (Chrysler) bastards who built these trucks in this era used the most god awful clear coat known to man, so the paint is sun faded, and they used the same ass backwards technology in the dash caps, so they always crack. This dash has a few holes that you can fit a Tijuana hooker through, but I fixed that silly problem by throwing a dash cover over it and forgetting about it. The only other things on the truck that I know about are the clockspring in the steering wheel needed replaced, as well as the blend door is starting to go out. 
 
Modifications- 
-RCD 6 inch lift, all spring in the front with true long arm suspension links (not the stamped stock control arms), lift blocks in the back. 
-35 inch Toyo Mud Terrains on Micky Thompson wheels. (May 015) 80% life. 
-Completely rebuilt rear axle (June 2015) with a Detroit Locker. 
-Completely rebuilt steering (August 2015) All Moog suspension tie rods and drag links, new steering box, Poison Spyder front diff cover 
-Flowmaster 50 series with turn downs.  
-Rockford Fosgate 12 inch subs with Kicker amp behind the seat. Pioneer deck in the dash.  
-Monster Transmission "Mega Monster" Rebuilt transmission, this was done less that 500 miles ago. It improves various weak spots of the transmission, the drivetrain is now good for 500 hp. (I had plans for a 408 stroker engine, but things have changed). Also replaced the oil pan and rear main engine seal. 
-Finally, the one thing that everyone questions me about, the mushroom. When I bought the truck it had an Airaid intake that sucked water whenever I hit a puddle, so I welded up a custom box for it to seal it up, and piped it through the hood into a mushroom cap off of a M35 military truck. It works well, I run the truck through mud bogging competitions with zero issues. It also catches peoples' eyes when driving, I have seen people almost crash because they were trying to figure out what it was instead of driving. I figure it's what a pretty lady feels like when she wears a low cut shirt and causes guys to trip over themselves as they walk by. 
 
Everything is going with the truck that is in the bed, I won't be pulling the toolbox or the jerry can, those are yours. The original "full-size" spare is under the bed, and there is a full 35 inch spare in the bed that will go along with the truck as well. The price is $6500obo. Please no trades or payments. Sweet green cash only. Call or text with questions, 520-5zero7-three60five. I will list the $1000 worth extra parts that I have in the toolbox that go along with it as well. Don't need help selling. 
 
Parts- 
-Full power steering lines 
-New power steering pump 
-Hughes Engines Plenum kit 
-NGK Iridium ix spark plugs 
-MSD super conductor plug wires 
-Accel performance ignition coil and adaptor 
-Monster Tranfer Case rebuild kit 
-Hayden 405 auxiliary trans cooler 
-Fel-pro engine seal kit 
-OEM replacement distributor 
-Cloyes timing chain 
-Shift tech 46re shit kit (went with a transgo system upon rebuild) 
-RCD bushing kit for the link, this includes replacement johnny joints 
- A few other seals and grommets along with the stock front diff cover.

title: Yamaha 6.1 Channel 630 Watt AV Receiver
description:
Yamaha 6.1 Channel 630 Watt AV Receiver  
 
Up for sale is a loud and clear playing Yamaha AM/FM AV Receiver in excellent condition- The model number is HTR-5850. This is a 6.1 receiver with subwoofer out/control.  
 
Operation manual is readily available online in PDF format.  
 
This receiver will play iPod and other mobile device/Mp3 players through a typical $4 RCA cord. Unit is being offered at a very reasonable $70.00.  
 
 
 
Product Description 
Y 
amaha 6.1-Channel 630W (105W x 6) A/V Receiver. It features Yamaha's unique CINEMA DSP for outstandfing home theater performance, as well all Dolby formats and all DTS formats. It has Quad-Field CINEMA DSP and 14 Surround programs. It also features Night Listening Enhancer (Cinema/Music) and Silent Cinema. It has Component Video Up Conversion (Full) It is XM Satellite Radio ready. It has a Slectable 9-Band Subwoofer Crossover/Subwoofer Phase Selector. 
 
The Yamaha HTR-5850 XM-ready digital hometheater receiver is a full-featured digital home theater receiver that sports some serious features. Component video-up conversion takes composite signals and converts them into a component signal. This not only ensures the highest quality video from any source, it means you only need one connection to your HDTV monitor. No more switching inputs according to your source--it can all go through the component video connection. 
 
Some other major features on the Yamaha HTR-5850 include 6.1-channel discrete amplification (105 w x 6 RMS) and Yamaha's Digital ToP-ART (Total Purity Audio Reproduction Technology) amplifier design concept that ensures the highest signal purity, and 14 surround programs. Also featured is Silent Cinema, Yamaha's exclusive technology that allows private listening enjoyment of multichannel music or movie sound, including Dolby Digital and DTS Digital Surround, through ordinary headphones. The system's digital-to-analog converters use an extremely high performance 192 kHz/24-bit operation type and perform accurate sound field reproduction for high-quality multichannel sources. And for two-channel stereo, they provide outstanding separation and precise musical delineation. In addition, the HTR-5850-SL has high-quality two-channel and multichannel surround reproduction and reproduces surround for 5.1 channels and 2.1 (virtual surround). The HTR-5850 is also XM Satellite Radio ready, which means that with the addition of an XM Connect-and-Play and XM subscription, you can tune into your favorite XM broadcasts. 
 
The HTR-5850 also features Yamaha's exclusive Quad-Field Cinema Digital Sound Field Processing, or DSP--Yamaha's way of recreating the ambiance of a stadium, a concert hall, or an intimate club in the comfort of your own home. With 14 different sound programs that provide multiple variations, every movie and every piece of music will sound right in your home theater. Discrete power transistors, rather than chips, are used in the amplifier section to provide the cleanest sound possible. The amp delivers 105 watts each to seven channels, and the HTR-5850 can accommodate DVD, CD, MC/CDR, and digital TV/cable. Three optical digital outputs assure the finest possible signal leaving the receiver for your other components. A set of front panel A/V inputs allows for simple temporary connection. The receiver also features an AM/FM digital tuner with 40 station presets.

title: Diamondback Carbon Racing Bike - 13lbs SRAM Red HED Carbon Wheels $8k
description:
Diamondback Podium Equipe Red 22 Road Bike (56cm). This bike weighs 13.5 lbs. That is insanely light. Most high-end sub $10,000 bikes weight 16lbs or higher. This bike is a rocket! 
 
I am asking $3,500 for the complete bike. Brand new, never ridden. PRICE JUST LOWERED! I need to sell this bike. 
 
The retail price on this bike is $8,000. This is the same exact bike (frame and specs) that Diamondback's professional team races on. The frame technology comes from Cervelo and Look bikes. The components are the highest end SRAM set - SRAM Red 22 speed. The wheels are HED Stinger 4 Aero Carbon wheels. The wheels retail for $2100; the SRAM Red 22 set retails for $2,400. At my $4,000 asking price you are essentially buying the components and wheels and getting the frame and carbon parts for free. 
 
The frame is 56cm - their size Medium / Large. It is designed to fit 5'9" to 6'1" heights. 
 
I bought this bike brand new for myself. It's too aggressive for my needs. I decided to go with a gravel bike instead. So I'm selling this Diamondback. 
 
You can text me at 4-8-zero-four-four-2-four-zero-2-9. Mention that you are interested in the Diamondback bike when you text because I have a few bikes and things for sale on Craigslist. 
 
-- 
 
Road Bike Actions has this to say about the Diamondback Podium Equipe Red 22: 
 
Diamondback took a balanced approach to ride quality rather than just going in with the stiffer-is-better approach. Even the pentagon-shaped downtube and rectangular chainstays aren't noticeably overbuilt. The top tube takes on a wide but quite thin profile, which is shared by the seatstays-both are clearly focused on compliance. As you'd expect from Diamondback's premier race bike, geometry is, well, racy. It uses parallel, 73-degree seat and head tube angles (56cm frame) with a 98.4cm wheelbase- pretty standard fare for the bike's intended purpose. 
 
Straight off the bat everyone agreed that it was one of the more comfortable pro race bikes we had ridden. The small vibrations that typically resonate through us when riding some other flagship race bikes were mostly absent on the Podium Equipe. 
 
Adding to the positive first impressions was its downright luxuriously light, 14-pound weight, which added to the enjoyment factor while climbing. Of course, you have to remember that the tubular HED wheels are a critical aspect to the bike's low weight and impressive ride quality. 
 
 
 
Diamondback Podium Equipe Red 22 Road Bike 
 
The Diamondback Podium Equipe is a top of the line carbon competition road racing machine. From the aggressive carbon shapes to the latest internal cable housing design, this is the ultimate road frame. The frame comes in at under 900 grams thanks to the newly designed tapered Continuous Fiber Technology full carbon fork with integrated carbon crown race. Diamondback set out to create a road bike that is more user and performance friendly, not just for the top racers of the world but also the weekend road warriors that ride thousands of miles a year. 
 
Diamondback looked at the handling, feel, weight, and geometry of each frame and each size so they could make sure every product has the signature Diamondback feel. Then Diamondback does conceptual sketches, 3D Modeling, and Finite Element Analysis (FEA) before they even make the first steel mold. They set clear and concise goals to make the Podium a world-class frame and they strive to make an already incredible product. . .better. Diamondback feels that only after going through all these long, tedious processes that this is the only way to create a high performance racing bicycle worthy of the Podium badge. 
 
Continuous Fiber -- Diamondback's Continuous Fiber Technology uses full-length carbon strands to manufacture the fork that extend from the top of the steerer tube to the bottom of the drop outs. Using that same AMMP technology employed in the Podium frame, they've created one of the stiffest forks available. With a lower integrated crown race that's completely carbon, they've eliminated the need for a separate aluminum race. This makes the overall system lighter, stronger and more responsive. 
Tapered Head Tube -- 1.5 Tapered head tube provides front end torsional stiffness for precise steering and control. 
Compliant Stays -- Seat tube and seat stays are designed to work together to produce an optimally compliant ride. 
Pressfit 30 --An oversized BB shell coupled with a larger down tube and chain stays provides increased rigidity for out-of-the saddle-sprinting, maximum acceleration, and optimal efficiency. 
Closed Circuit Cabling -- Closed Circuit Cable routing provides a clean, uncluttered, and sleek finish to the frame. 
Replaceable Front Derailleur Hanger -- lightweight and easy to mount in the correct position. . . every time.

description:
AMPEG & GENZ BENZ BASS AMPS  & CABS FOR SALE!!!!! 
 
AMPEG SVT 4-PRO $550 *SOLD* 
 
Up for sale is my Ampeg SVT 4PRO bass head. Amp is US made and in great condition. This head gets VERY loud!!! Will include rack for additional $25. Tuner and power conditioner NOT INCLUDED!! See the specs below: 
 
RMS Power Output: 300-Watts x 2/900 (mono-bridged @ 8 Ohms) 
RMS Power Output: 490-Watts x 2/1200 (mono-bridged @ 4 Ohms) 
RMS Power Output (2 Ohms): 600-Watts x 2

Tone Controls: 3-Band

Graphic EQ: Yes, 9-Band
