Balanced Line Out: Yes x 2 Pre/Post with Level 
Effects Loop: Yes x 2 
Preamp Out/Power Amp In: Yes x 2 
Dimensions (W x H x D inches): 19 x 5.6 x 15.5 
Weight: 39.5 Pounds 
 
AMPEG SVT-100 ALL TUBE BASS HEAD  $575 
 
MTI-ERA AMPEG. Want that huge SVT sound without the weight or extreme volume? Here you go!! 100 Pure Tube Watts!!! Great for bass or guitar. Huge Sound!! Great condition for a vintage amp.  
 
SVT-100  
Preamp: 3 x 12AX7  
Power: 4 x 6550  
Single channel, two inputs  
6 knobs (V,MV,B,M,T,P) bs, gain switch  
 
VINTAGE AMPEG SVT BASS AMPLIFIER  $700 
 
For sale is a vintage Ampeg SVT all tube bass amp. 300 all tube watts!! This thing is LOUD!!! She may not be pretty but she sounds AMAZING!!! According to the original owners this was purchased in 1979. It looks like an MTI era SVT tho (the change happened in 1980). It is possibly one of the very early transition models but no way to know for sure. The serial number tag is missing from the back and I have not opened it to look inside. According to the original owners this was a rental that toured the country for years. Supposedly used by Jason Newsted in his Flotsam years, but again no way to know that for sure. Either way, this is a killer sounding amp. Both channels work great!  
 
I bought this amp with the intention of refurbishing it and making it look as good as it sounds. Unfortunately I have a family situation that requires making some sacrifices. I am offering this head at the same price that I paid for it almost 2 months ago.  
 
The details: 
 
The Good: 
The head sounds like it should: loud, aggressive, growly, beautiful.  
Head is solid and both channels work as they should.  
Good overall physical condition with some tolex damage, but nothing major.  
All rocker switches work correctly. 
It's a vintage Ampeg SVT!!! 
 
The Bad: 
The faceplate has clearly been written on with a paint pen but there are enough of the dial markings left to see what settings you are using.  
Fan is loud but you will NOT hear it while you are playing. 
On/Off switch stays "on" so you just use the "Standby" switch  
Slight tolex damage. 
 
Look at the pictures but the head does look better in person (because the pictures really suck). I really hate to sell this but sometimes you gotta do what you gotta do. The price is $700 FIRM and that is a LOCAL PICKUP PRICE ONLY!!!! I am not looking to ship this amp at this time. I am also not going to deal with you "shipping agent", accept a money order, or take payments.  
 
If you want that vintage Ampeg SVT sound for a lot less money then this is the amp for you. Please text me if you are interested and want to set up a test. I have a bass and speaker cab you can use to test it with.  
 
GENZ BENZ 212 XB CAB  $200 OBO 
 
Genz Benz 212XB cab with adjustable tweeter in great condition. Handles 350 watts and is an 8 ohm cabinet and sounds fantastic with the SVT-100!!! Has wheels and a handle so easy to move around.  
 
AMPEG BXT115 Cabinet $175 OBO 
 
Ampeg 1X15" with adjustable tweeter. 400 Watts at 4 ohms. Good condition and sounds great!!! Has casters so easy to move.  
 
Will consider a package deal for one of the heads and one of the speaker cabs. Prices on the heads are pretty firm but I am reasonable.

title: 2009 Pivot Mach 5, MSRP: $4,885 without upgraded $1,000 wheels
description:
2009 Pivot Mach 5, MSRP: $4,885 without upgraded $1,000 wheels. 
 
This ride is built to be a light, fast, all mountain machine.  
 
Research the reviews on the frame and the parts. This is easily over a $6k bike at more than 75% off. 
 
Offering to let this go at a steel of a price, $1695.  
 
•	Make: Pivot 
•	Model: Mach 5 
•	Model year: 2009 
•	Size: M  
•	Color: Anodized graphite grey 
•	Wheel size: 26"  
Bike would easily cost $4k in used As-Is condition with these parts and frame if this was a 29er. The larger wheel size is nice, but not always the best way to go if you're not looking to spend over $2k on a used bike. This bike is a steal because 26" wheels are out of favor, but that really means value riders can get a lot more bang for the buck. 
 
•	Rear travel: 140mm 
•	Frame material: Aluminum alloy 
•	Suspension description: dw-link w/ sealed bearings 
•	Rear shock: Fox RP23 high volume with Boost Valve 
•	Fork: Fox 32 Float 140 FIT RLC, 15 QR, with 1 1/8" straight steerer  
(This is an $800 fork. Kashima-coated stanchions, Adjustable rebound, low-speed compression, crown mounted lockout with variable lockout sensitivity, and air spring pressure...loads of external adjustments so you can really dial in your fork) 
•	Handlebar: Ritchey Pro WCS 
•	Stem: Ritchey Pro WCS 
•	Headset: Ritchey Pro WCS 
•	Bottom bracket: Shimano XTR 
•	Crank: Shimano XT 
•	Pedals: N/A 
•	Saddle: WTB Silverado RC 
•	Seatpost : Ritchey Pro WCS  
•	Front derailleur: Shimano XTR 
•	Rear derailleur: Shimano XT 
•	Shifters: Shimano XT 
•	Cassette: ShimanoXT 
•	Brakes: Shimano XT 
•	Grips: Specialized Lock-on 
•	Cassette: Sram 11-34t, 9-speed 
Wheels: Wheels are custom built for extra stiffness, low weight and improved control. Tubeless setup reduces flats, weight and improves control. 
•	Rims: Stans ZTR Arch -- "Proven in the Enduro World Series, but light enough to be a favorite among XC racers everywhere" 
•	Hubs:  Hope EVO Pro 2 -- Front wheel has 15 QR thru-axle for added stiffness and control. 
•	Tires: Maxxis Ardent (front), Maxxis Ikon (rear) 
**Weight without pedals: 27lbs. 
 
Included items with bike: OEM Pivot Sag meter, Anodized Red Salsa seat clamp, OEM Pivot Stem Cap. 
 
 
The Pivot Cycles Mach 5 was made to perform during long days in the saddle. With a full 5.3" of travel, the Mach 5 is positioned right between our Mach 4 and Mach 5.7, making it the ultimate trail bike with the soul of a cross country rig. It's meant to cover the spectrum of 24 hour racing and all-day in-the-saddle rides, with the ability to devour technical descents. 
Wherever and whatever you ride, the Mach 5 will make your experience much more enjoyable. With 5.3" of precision-tuned dw-link(r) travel, unparalleled frame stiffness, and our custom-tuned Fox suspension with Boost Valve technology, the Mach 5 delivers an incredibly efficient, balanced feel. Descend with confidence as your Mach 5 soaks up everything from small bumps to the biggest hits, delivering superior plushness and control. As the trail turns up, the Mach 5 exhibits exceptional climbing traction. If you had to own only one bike, the Mach 5 is it. 
The ride: The Mach 5 has the distinction of winning the 2009 MTBR award for Best Full-Suspension All-Mountain Bike. With 5.3" of travel, the Mach 5 is designed and built to be the ultimate bike for wherever your ride. The Mach 5 can easily conquer a 24-hour race one weekend, then bring a smile to your face the next weekend as you put in an all-day ride with friends on your favorite trail system. 
And when the terrain turns rough, the Mach 5 shines. We have tested this bike everywhere from South Mountain's National Trail to Moab's Porcupine Rim. The Mach 5 holds its line at speed and always seems to have extra travel in reserve for big hits, big drops, and even the occasional big jump. The Mach 5 features a dw-link(r) suspension design, which allows the bike to devour technical descents, yet avoids any inefficient, squishy feel. The head angle with the fork at 140mm travel is 69 degrees. This is a nice stable number for handling very technical terrain. The Mach 5 is all about achieving a balance in what we believe to be the perfect combination of incredible pedaling efficiency and frame stiffness with a controlled feel throughout the stroke and enough travel to keep our customers grinning from ear to ear in even some of the most technical terrain.  
 
Welds: The Mach 5 uses a combination of traditional welds and smooth welds. The smooth welds on some bikes are polished out after being completed (a la Cannondale). We like the flat bead look of the smooth weld as it is laid down. We use it near on the top tube shock tab area to keep things smooth and snag free and on other areas because it actually reduces stress risers and makes for a nice strong joint.

title: TRAXXAS SLASH 1/10 2WD ELECTRIC SHORT COURSE TRUCK 58034-1
description:
The award-winning Traxxas Slash Short-Course Race Truck puts you in the drivers seat for intense fender-to-fender, high-flying off-road action. The full-scale Short-Course Race Trucks embody the spirit of Traxxas R/C with their extreme 900+ horsepower racing engines full-throttle, dirt-roosting power slides, giant suspension travel, and Supercross-style big-air jumps. The Traxxas Slash brings all the action home so you can experience the high-speed head-to-head competition at the track or in your own backyard. The Slash was inspired by the TORCâ¢ (THE Traxxas Off-Road Championshipâ¢) Pro 2WD class. The Pro 2WD class specifies rear-wheel drive trucks purpose built to fly over jumps and rip full-throttle through the turns. The Traxxas Slash hangs it out for an all new way to challenge your driving skills. The 4-wheel independent suspension has been carefully tuned to replicate the Pro 2 driving and handling experience as closely as possible. The scale appearing tires provide just the right amount of bite and thick, blinding clouds of dirt roost. When the racing action cools down, the Traxxas Slash is well-equipped to tackle all of your off-track driving adventures. The long travel suspension and oil-filled shocks easily absorb jumps and rough terrain. The unique chassis design provides huge center ground clearance to drive over deep ruts, rocks, and other obstacles that leave ordinary R/C trucks stuck. The tires use advanced tread design and sophisticated rubber compounds to provide incredible grip off-road with enough versatility to also perform well on concrete and asphalt. The fenders cover the tires so you bang against your driving buddies without getting tangled up. The Revo-spec Torque-Controlâ¢ slipper clutch design delivers smooth operation, precise adjustment, and consistent traction control. The bellcrank steering system virtually eliminates bump steer for precise handling and control. A digital steering servo delivers lightning fast response. Traxxas shocked enthusiasts with the release of our exclusive watertight, sealed electronics in the E-Maxx that provided the freedom to drive where you want to drive through water, mud, snow, and other wet-running conditions that wouldn't have been possible before. The proven XL-5 electronic speed control and the mini receiver are sealed against the elements giving you the freedom go places you might not have thought possible. It opens up a whole new world of adventure and fun. Wet muddy tracks are no problem for the Slash. The battery compartment makes it easy to install batteries and the clever design makes it quickly adaptable for either 6 or 7-cell running (hump packs or stick packs).The Titan 12T 550 modified motor is designed for incredible mod-motor power output with virtually maintenance-free operation, and long-lasting performance. The Titan 12T 550 motor's integrated cooling fan pulls cool air through the motor to keep temperatures down. Airflow is routed through vent tunnels molded in the motor plate. A cooler running motor equates to faster speeds, longer runtime, and extended motor life. The XL-5 Electronic Speed Control offers high current handling, EZ-SetÂ® one-button setup, and smooth high-frequency control. Three drive profiles, low voltage detection, thermal shutdown protection, gold-plated connectors, and incredibly low resistance are all features you might expect to only be available on an expensive replacement ESC. As today's batteries store more and more energy inside their cells, traditional battery connectors could no longer keep up. The included patented Traxxas High-Current Connector opens the door for unrestricted current flow. With the TQâ¢ 2.4GHz radio system, you just switch on a drive. There are no channels or frequencies to manage, so the focus is on having fun. The TQ's ergonomic design is comfortable for all-day driving, and its sleek lines are enhanced by an internal antenna that is impervious to damage. Traxxas' exclusive patented Training Mode let's everyone get in on the racing action. Just press a button to limit full-throttle power to 50%. This allows young or new drivers to safely develop their control skills before unlocking full power to the mighty Titan 12T motor. The Slash is perfect for drivers at all experience levels. Training mode even makes it easy to hand the transmitter over to your friends who have never driven a radio controlled truck before. The Traxxas Slash model 58034 comes fully-assembled and Ready-To-RaceÂ® with the TQ radio system installed and adjusted, XL-5 power system, Power Cell 7-cell NiHM battery, wall charger, a painted and decaled body, pre-glued tires, and detailed instructions. There's a reason this powerful RC machine is a classic. Add it to your RC arsenal today. 
 
Fully assembled and ready to race! 
Precision TQ 2.4 GHz Radio Control System  
Water-proof electronics to survive races in all the elements. 
Titan 12 Turn 550 Modified Motor for maintenance free, maximum power. 
XL-5 Waterproof Electronic Speed Control 
New advanced 4-amp DC Peak Detecting Fast Charger

title: TRAXXAS SLASH 1/10 4X4 ELECTRIC SHORT COURSE TRUCK 68086-21
description:
This Slash 4X4 is hard-loaded for ultimate performance and realism with the Traxxas On-Board Audio, new Traxxas Stability Management (TSM) and a low-CG chassis. Traxxas On-Board Audio delivers the full short course experience with the powerful and loud sound of a 900 horsepower engine ripping through the gears. While TSM and the Low CG chassis combine for a whole new level of speed and precision behind the wheel.  
 
Traxxas Stability Management (TSM) allows you to experience all the extreme power, speed, and acceleration that was engineered into the Slash 4X4 by making it much easier to control on common slippery surfaces such as loose dirt, smooth concrete, and even ice and snow. Punch it off the line and TSM goes to work sensing the vehicle's direction and making steering corrections to provide straight-ahead full-throttle acceleration without fishtailing, spinouts, and loss of control. TSM also works during cornering, first making intuitive corrections to maintain your line, and then allowing you to hammer the throttle earlier in the turn for much faster exit speeds. Braking is dramatically improved as TSM works to keep you arrow straight until you come to a complete stop. TSM acts as your on-board co-pilot in the vehicle that "feels" what the vehicle is doing and makes corrections for vehicle movements that you cannot even detect, well before the vehicle gets out of control.  
 
Traxxas TSM gives you all the benefits modern electronic stabilization has to offer without intruding on your driving fun. Traxxas engineers developed superior tuning algorithms that run on high-speed, precision electronic components to create a system that works invisibly, in the background, without ever limiting your throttle. TSM can be fine tuned (or turned off) for different surfaces by simply adjusting the multi-function knob on the TQi transmitter, or by adjusting the slider in the Traxxas link app. The result is that you are driving faster, with more ease, and having more fun,with that fully connected feeling at the controls that you expect. In fact, you may not even realize how much TSM is helping you until you turn it off and test your driving skills without it! 
 
On-Board Audio System 
The On-Board Audio System uses sound that has been sampled from Traxxas team trucks, including the Traxxas Pro 4 short course truck driven by Traxxas' Mike Jenkins. The ON/OFF button and volume controls let you adjust the system settings, stealth mode to wide-open. The system uses a minimal amount of power from the battery so your runtime is not compromised. The intuitive sounds respond to throttle input from the transmitter. Cruise around or rip full-throttle to hear the difference in engine RPM. If you're stopped for more than 10 seconds, the engine will shut off. Just tap the throttle to hear the engine fire back up! Use the rocker switch on the included 3-channel transmitter to shift to "neutral" and hear the engine revving. Flip the switch, and launch back into racing. 
 
Class-Leading Brushless Power 
 
Slash 4X4's Traxxas Velineon Brushless Power system defines a whole new generation of outrageous electric power that doesn't know limitations and boundaries. Pour in the voltage and out comes the speed in tidal waves of force harnessed by precision throttle control. For the uninitiated, prepare yourself... the sheer brutal power combined with the Slash 4X4's four-corner grip results in tire-melting acceleration and lightning fast speed. The Velineon 3s Brushless Power System features system components that work together as an optimized package, from the patented Traxxas High-Current connector to the custom-wound motor. It's engineered together from the start to deliver the ultimate in efficiency, speed, and run-time along with precision throttle response and refined control. It's brushless performance the Traxxas way: wicked fast and easy to use. Just plug it in and it works, no special knowledge or programming skills required. 
 
Velineon VXL-3s Electronic Speed Control 
The Velineon VXL-3s speed control is loaded with high-grade technology to precisely deliver maximum power to the motor. It's engineered for today's battery technology and beyond. Two-stage low voltage detection allows full LiPo compatibility, including powerful 11.1-volt 3S packs! 
 
Velineon 3500 Brushless Motor 
Extreme performance is standard equipment with the sensorless Velineon motor. Ultra high-temperature Neodymium magnets, high-speed ball bearings, and a precision balanced rotor deliver power and long life with near zero maintenance. Since there are no brushes or commutator to wear out, you always get the same blistering acceleration and ballistic top speed run after run. 
 
 
 
Larger pinion gear/smaller spur gear combinations are for high-speed running on hard, smooth surfaces only. 
 
  
 
Precision 2.4GHz Control 
 
Traxxas Slash 4X4 OBA is equipped with the world's most advanced Ready-To-RaceÂ® radio system. The all-new TraxxasÂ® TQiâ„¢ arrives with a full complement of tuning features and offers the unbeatable convenience of "no channels, no crystals" 2.4GHz technology--but that's just the beginning. Automatic model recognition instantly recalls your settings for up to 30 Traxxas Link-enabled models. Just switch on and drive, no naming or "model memory" settings required. Power up the transmitter and the model you want to drive, and the settings for that model are dialed in immediately! The new TQi 2.4GHz transmitter is fully adjustable: steering and throttle end points can be set precisely, and the Multi-Function knob can be programmed to control Steering Sensitivity (Expo), Throttle Sensitivity (Expo), Steering Percentage (Dual Rate), Braking Percentage (Dual Rate), or Throttle Trim. TQi's ergonomic case design provides all-day driving comfort, and the unique internal antenna contributes to its sleek, modern look. 
 
Equipped with Low-CG Chassis 
 
Slash 4X4's performance refinements begin with Low-CG (low center of gravity) chassis that's unlike anything you've seen before. The battery and electronics are held as deep in the chassis as possible to position weight low in the chassis. Arrow-straight, hard-charging acceleration with Extreme Brushless Power and 4WD requires a chassis that won't flex under load. To offer the necessary rigidity, the chassis is reinforced by integrated ribs that form a triangulated structure optimized for the loads imparted by the suspension and powertrain. Underneath, the chassis is ultra-smooth to reduce drag and prevent snags whether you're blasting through whoops on the track or blazing trails in your backyard. The low-CG design dramatically increases corner speed and stability no matter where you drive. On the racecourse, Slash 4X4's low center of gravity allows high-output Velineon brushless power to be channeled into the track with superior traction, resulting in harder launches and faster lap times. 
 
Authentic Short-Course Style 
Slash 4X4's Race Replica bodies are fully decorated with licensed logos and graphics for total authenticity. In addition to the no. Each truck is equipped with an accurate representation of the full-size tire, giving Slash 4X4 the ultimate in realistic performance and control. Wheels complete the look; offering equal parts style and strength, Slash 4X4 features a new SCT Split Spoke design and color-molded "beadlock" detail. Fully compatible with factory Traxxas and aftermarket tires, the wheels also feature 12mm hexes and the same offset as Slash 2WD rear wheels. 
 
100% Fully Assembled and Ready-To-RaceÂ® 
 
Slash 4X4 comes fully-assembled and Ready-To-RaceÂ® with the TQi 2.4GHz radio system installed and adjusted, Velineon brushless power system, a painted and decaled body, pre-glued tires, and detailed instructions. Traxxas backs Slash 4X4 and all of our products with top-notch support that is second to none. A staff of skilled representatives is on-hand to answer your questions via phone, website, or e-mail. Unmatched parts support allows Slash 4X4 to be serviced with parts and support from thousands of hobby dealers worldwide. Your investment is also protected by the Traxxas Lifetime Electronics Warranty. Traxxas goes the extra mile to ensure that your R/C experience is easy and fun (and fast!). Follow the details link above to go in depth on all the Slash 4X4 performance benefits and also be sure to check out the videos page to see Slash 4X4 in action for yourself.

title: SONY HDR-XR550 Cam Corder Video Camera
description:
Exceptional Video Recorder.  SONY HRD-XR550 has 240Gb  oh on-board disk storage or 91 hours of HD video.  Ever since I've owned this I've never had to download and delete, it just never fills up! 
The results from this camera when displayed on a wide screen via the HDMI cable are astounding. 
The capture in dark evenings is fantastic as is the sound quality. 
I just don't seem to use it as much I should, kids grown up, so iPhone will do instead. 
Excellent condition, Complete with additional large capacity battery, charger (obvious), several cables including HDMI, manual and remote control.  Plus two tripods (one as in photo, the other a pocket one), plus cleaning kit. 
Here's a review from the web... 
 
Sony always wants to go the extra mile and its latest Full HD shooter, complete with 240GB hard drive, has the capacity to put the 32GB and 64GB storage of rival cams well and truly in the shade. 
Favoring HDD (hard disk drive) over flash memory, the chunky and robust HDR-XR550 can store up to 101 hours of movies and stills. But it doesn't end there. Sony has opened up the XR550 to SD card recording as well as its traditional Memory Stick media, so insert an extra card of your choice and you'll increase recording potential still further. 
Touch sensitive 
Built for folks who are serious about their video, this cam uses a wide-angle G lens (26.3mm stills, 29.8mm video) that lets you cram loads more into a scene without the need to keep moving further away from your subject. It's perfect for landscape shots but works just as well for group shots. No one gets left out of the frame this time. 
The pro-credentials are enhanced by the inclusion of a viewfinder and a superbly responsive 3.5in touchscreen LCD. You can use it to compose shots, browse the extensive but practical onscreen menu, and perhaps best of all review your footage on a screen that doesn't make you squint at what you're supposed to be watching. 
A manual focus and exposure ring to the side of the lens adds another level of user control over image taking, while an intuitive image stabilizer delivers something labelled as three-way shake cancelling -- which in plain speak means you get smoother shots no matter what end of the 10x optical zoom you're shooting at.

$475 is a great deal.

It is in perfect condition and needs nothing at all. If you are not familiar with the Deuces, they were limited edition bikes designed by Willie G. Davidson himself. Some features of the Deuce are: more front end rake, longer, lower and stretched fuel tank, lower/longer seat, bigger rear tire (160/70-17,) polished aluminum rear wheel, 21" spoke front tire, shorter rear fender, more chrome, and they were the first bikes to use the smaller bullet, tuck in turn signals. These bikes have a longer, lower, sleeker look than a normal Softail, a lower seat height, and better handling too.  It is powered by a fuel injected Twin Cam 88 engine, and it runs perfectly. This bike has Cobra dual exhaust with a crossover chamber, and a stage II  HP air cleaner for higher performance and better fuel mileage. It also has a Halogen headlight, and Flame style grips too. Since we love the Deuces and both of us have had several, we have other seats, (including a reduced reach touring seat), V&H Pro pipe, tach, and some other chrome goodies, available if you wish. Always garaged and covered. Extremely clean condition! Trade possible.  Timm

title: 2006 Scion xA Sale/trade
description:
Just out to test the waters and see what kind of offers I get. I have a 2006 Scion xA, I've owned it for just over 3 years and bought it completely stock but I've invested a lot of time, money and effort into it to make it a handling streetable car.  
Modifications include- 
- ksport kontrol pro coilovers/swift 200kg rear springs (ksport springs included) 
- hotchkis rear 24mm anti-sway bar 
- Megan racing H-brace  
- DC Sports front strut bar 
- Megan racing rear c-pillar brace connected to a 1 off z "cage" 
- Minor weight reduction (approx. 100lbs) 
- FRS seats (just need to hook up seat connectors, still plan on doing so anyways) 
- Rear windshield wiper delete (virtually useless anyways) 
- StopTech Cryo-treated slotted rotors/ Hawk HPS Street compound pads 
- Energy Suspension front sway bar bushings 
-XXR 513 powder coated wrapped in Bridgestone Potenza Re760s sport tires 
(Note* wheels werent pretty when I bought them, used to be driven not to be pretty.) 
- TRD Glass Fog Lights w/ 3k bulbs (clean install) 
- lots of minor touches with LED lights (interior/exterior) 
- ZXE Headlight bulbs, much whiter and brighter than factory 
- DC Sports SRI 
- OBX-R 4-2-1 stainless header w/ heatshield mounts 
- New rear OEM bumper (unpainted) 
- New OEM wing spoiler (flint mica, not indigo pearl) it doesn't bother me they're not matching, planned on wrapping it in the future 
- UltraGauge OBDII data plug-in, real time vehicle data display  
- Brand new Toyota Thermostat, seal, and coolant 3000 miles ago (routine maint. And was time for a flush) 
Cons- 
- Automatic 
- Cracked front windshield 
- Hail damage 
- Salvage title because of ^^ 
- Trashed paint due to sun exposure 
Again, the car wasn't meant to be the cleanest, it really was just a hold over car till I found something better, but I kinda fell with the idea that no body has one especially like this, its an interesting car for sure. It runs and drive absolutely perfect, never had a single problem with it ever. Oil changed every 3500 miles with mobile 1 advanced full synthetic 5w-30. Has 148,XXX miles, will go up slowly, I drive it once or twice a week. Blows cold A/C and hell temps heat. 
Have a full box of parts I've accumulated over the years, and the rear seats can go with, bit has a little bit of white paint on a part of it from a little mishap. I know I don't have pics of everything, bit willing to send pics upon request. Again, no rush to sell just testing the waters. It really is fun to drive, I know I've always wished it was a 5-speed too, but its really kind of suprising. Interested in something RWD or AWD and MUST be manual. Would love something like a 90s 325i, e36, variants of 240sx(s13/14), anything cool. Make an offer, worst I can say is no, thanks anyways.  
Any questions, just ask. 
Thanks for looking. 
60two - 70five - four574

title: Traktor Kontrol S4 DJ Controller
description:
I have been using this for years and is in great condition. I recently moved up to the S8 model so this is now available. Below are details about the product: 
 
Native Instruments revolutionized the DJ world nearly a decade ago with the introduction of TRAKTOR, the world's first professional DJ software. Now they're back at it again with TRAKTOR KONTROL S4, a DJ performance system designed from the ground up from the team behind TRAKTOR. Note:Free update to the new TRAKTOR PRO 2 software for registered S4 users. See Native Instrument's website for latest software and firmware updates. The New Performance DJ System Forget what you know about DJ controllers and DJ software. TRAKTOR KONTROL S4 was designed from its conception as a fully integrated system where software and hardware are fused in perfect harmony. Once you experience it, you'll immediately feel how simple, yet powerful and fluid a professional DJ system can be. TRAKTOR KONTROL S4 is the culmination of a 10-year vision and experience only Native Instruments can provide. So whether you're a seasoned TRAKTOR user looking for the ultimate controller, or just entering the world of digital DJing, the S4 delivers. Custom-tailored for TRAKTOR, the S4 fuses a premium-quality 4-channel DJ mixer, a built-in 24-bit/96kHz soundcard, an intuitive controller, and the flagship TRAKTOR PRO S4 software into one fully professional solutionthe ideal one-stop package for DJs who want pro features, instant usability and go-anywhere portability. KONTROL In Action The sleek, stylish controller puts TRAKTOR at your fingertipsfusing hardware and software into one harmonic unit. Innovative Sample Decks, high-quality electromagnetic jog wheels, two effect units, and two clearly laid-out deck control sections can be assigned to any of the four software decks and deliver a new level in creative control over your one shots, tracks, and loops. The intuitive and ergonomic controller layout and its robust rotary knobs provide precise visual and tactile status feedbackperfect for any DJ situation. Highly responsive to the touch, TRAKTOR KONTROL S4 is incredibly smooth to use.

title: Triathlon/Time Trial bike - Fuji Aloha
description:
Hello, 
I am selling my triathlon bike.  I'm just doing sprints now and don't need a Tri bike.  I'll just be riding my road bike.  I'm willing to sell it with its stock wheels with brand new tubes and brand new Michelin tires for $650 or with a set of Campagnolo Eurus light weight wheels with brand new Thick Slick tires and brand new tubes for $800.  The bike is a 10 speed Shimano Ultegra bike.  Campy wheelset has Shimano Ultegra 10 speed setup.  Bike has Profile Design bars and brand new red JagWire Pro shifter and brake cables, Brand new bar tape, brand new saddle mount two bottle cage, new number plate holder mounted in brake caliper hole on seat stay.  I purchased this bike a few months ago, spent tons of money getting it all set up to my liking and have decided to go a different route with my triathlon aspirations. Literally brand new cables, tires, tubes, cages, number plate bracket, bar tape and more.  I have a brand new, uninstalled Profile Design aero bottlet that mounts between the bars!  Never used.  I have the kit to mount it between wider bars, so there's tons of mounting options.  This was a $2500 bike when new and has been upgraded, maintained and tuned, so it's fresh and ready to go for its next owner.  Needs nothing but to be fitted to its new owner.  Tons of adjustability in these bikes!  I am 6'01" and typically ride a 59-60cm road bike and bought this from a 5'9"ish triathlete who would typically ride a 56cm road bike.  A lot more adjustment than a typical road bike.  The Aero carbon fiber seat post has tons of vertical adjustment and also has two configurations, allowing fore-aft adjustment of seat to change angle to bottom bracket.  For my asking price, I'll also throw in a brand new in sealed box (I could also install/set up the computer for you) Cateye Strada cycling computer!  The Fuji Aloha 1.0's were considerably more expensive than the Aloha 2.0's.  They had a nicer wheelset and upgraded components.  Shoot me an email response to the ad and I will respond via  
Email, text or call, whatever your preference!  
 
 
Specs: 
2009 Fuji Aloha 1.0 
red/black/white 
Shimano Ultegra f/r derailleur's 2x10 
10mm BCD  
FSA cranks, 172.5mm arm length 
53/39t  
Campagnolo Eurus wheelset  
Thick Slick 700cx25 tires - 2118mm rad. (Measured for super accurate computer measurement)

title: Ultimate Home Recording School
description:
The "Ultimate Home Recording School" DVD Box Set is our top of the line training set for the recording musician. 
 
 For more information go to http://blakesheltonlivecom.com 
 
 A 3-Disc set featuring over 6 Hours of Premium Hands On Training to help you master your home recording studio.Hosted by David Wills (Engineer/Consultant with Michael Jackson, Whitney Houston, Phil Collins), this is the one stop training on Home Recording that you've been looking for. 
 
 Basically, if you've ever wanted to have David spend the weekend at your house and teach you everything he has learned from working over 25 years with the best names in the business. . .this is your ticket to that experience. 
 
 Whether you use a software solution like Pro Tools, Cubase, Logic or Reason. . .or a hardware multitrack recorder, this massive library of training tutorials takes you from novice to expert. 
 
 All of our product specific training DVDs center on what buttons to press and what screens to navigate, but this set was developed to teach you the unchanging principles of Recording, Mixing & Mastering your songs. 
 
 There simply is no other training product like this that takes you through the entire home recording process in such complete way. 
 
 For more information go to http://blakesheltonlivecom.com 
 
 FREE BONUSES!! 
 
 Bonus #1 -- Project Files Folder 
 Each Ultimate Home Recording Box Set comes with exclusive DVD-ROM features on the 3rd DVD that includes project files, sample recordings with popular microphones, bonus videos and demos. . .and much, much more. We've also included some trial software of all the big names in the industry so that you can try plug ins, drum loops and recording/mastering software. 
 
 Bonus #2 -- EQ Cook Book 
 This E-Book includes all the tips & tricks in terms of EQ. All the bands of frequencies that instruments live in. . .all the EQ "neighborhoods" that we need to be familiar with. Plus a ton of online resources for in depth research on this subject. 
 
 Bonus #3 -- Effects Cook Book 
 Your ticket provides you access to this E-Book that gives you an entire E-Book filled with all the resources and online links to understand the effects world. 
 
 Bonus #4 -- How to make $$$ Six Figures working on Concert Tours 
 David Wills has toured the world working for the biggest names in the industry. Having days off in Rome, Moscow and Tokyo and pulling down six figures, life as a touring programmer/engineer is a rewarding one. For the first time ever, David goes into detail as to how to hunt down these jobs and make a living out of your passion. . .music! This E-Book is a valuable resource for anyone who would like to travel the world with the stars. . .and get paid well for it! 
 
 Bonus #5 -- Effects Training 
 Over 50 minutes of bonus training on a myriad of effects including Vocoders & Phasers, Flangers and Filters 
 
 For more information go to http://blakesheltonlivecom.com  
 
 
• Location: Phoenix, USA

title: M-Audio Profire 610 Audio Interface - Mint
description:
Selling my M-Audio Profire 610 Audio Interface along with both the firewire cable and a firewire PCI card that I've used with it. 
It's been well taken care of so it is not only in mint working condition but also still looks pretty much new. 
Price is firm. Cash and local pickup only. 
 
ProFire 610 
Designed by the company that revolutionized mobile music production, the ProFire™ 610 FireWire audio interface transforms your Mac or PC into a powerful 6-in/10-out recording studio. Premium digital converters deliver high-definition, 24-bit/192kHz audio throughout the signal path. Two preamps with award-winning Octane™ technology offer clean, transparent sound with low noise and exceptional headroom. Onboard DSP mixing provides a totally flexible recording experience--perfect for creating multiple, independent monitor mixes. The user-assignable master volume knob gives you flexible control over output levels. MIDI I/O allows you to connect keyboards and other outboard MIDI hardware. The half-rack-space unit also doubles as a standalone two-channel microphone preamp and A/D-D/A converter. ProFire 610 is compatible with major audio software including Pro Tools*, Cubase, Logic, Sonar, Live and GarageBand, making it an unbeatable choice for personal, high-definition recording. 
 
Continuing the Legacy 
The M-Audio® FireWire 410 audio interface helped ignite the mobile music revolution by delivering power and flexibility in a travel-friendly form factor. Musicians and producers tapped into a new level of creative freedom, using the FireWire 410 to make music in the field and on the go. ProFire 610 continues this legacy by introducing new features like Octane™ preamp technology, DSP mixing and high-definition, 24-bit/192kHz audio quality. By combining these professional, studio-grade tools in a half-rack-space unit, ProFire 610 delivers the most powerful mobile recording experience. 
Award-winning Octane Preamp Technology 
Great recordings start with great preamps. ProFire 610 brings you the same award-winning M-Audio Octane preamp technology that audio professionals trust for clean, transparent sound. Each preamp delivers low distortion and an extremely high signal-to-noise ratio--providing pristine audio fidelity right from the start of your signal path. In addition to exceptional sound, each preamp has a generous 73dB gain range**, 20dB pad and 48V phantom power. 
 
Onboard DSP Mixer 
ProFire 610 features an onboard DSP mixer, giving you an extra level of flexibility and improving the overall performance of your system. Use the software control panel to create custom configurations for different recording setups, then save the settings and instantly recall them later. You can set up five unique stereo mixes sourced from any of the hardware inputs and software returns simultaneously--ideal for assigning separate monitor mixes to multiple musicians. The onboard DSP mixer also enables you to monitor while tracking, just as you would with a hardware mixer. 
High-Definition 192kHz Sound and Solid Performance 
M-Audio designed the ProFire 610 using carefully selected components, including premium A/D-D/A converters that keep your audio signal uncolored and true to any input source. We engineered the electronic circuitry to provide an optimal signal path between input and output, resulting in extremely clean recordings that capture every nuance of your performance. ProFire 610 also features critically acclaimed JetPLL jitter-elimination technology for stable synchronization and exceptionally low audio band jitter. Building on M-Audio's time-proven FireWire driver technology--found in the best-selling FireWire 410 interface--ProFire 610 delivers solid performance and reliability at sample rates up to 24-bit/192kHz. 
 
User-Assignable Master Volume Control 
The ProFire 610 interface delivers flexible control over output levels, allowing you to create a monitoring setup tailored to your specific needs. The master volume knob can be assigned to attenuate all output pairs simultaneously--ideal for controlling a 7.1 surround mix. Alternatively, the master volume knob can control the levels sent to your main monitors, while headphone outputs 1 and 2 operate independently. With four analog output pairs and an intuitive software control panel, ProFire 610 offers a wide range of options for unique monitoring scenarios. 
Standalone Operation 
ProFire 610 also functions in standalone mode, allowing you to use its premium preamplifiers without connecting to a computer. Just power up ProFire 610, connect your microphones or instruments, and the preamp outputs automatically route to analog outputs 1 and 2, and S/PDIF. You can also connect digital devices via S/PDIF and convert to analog. This unique feature makes ProFire 610 ideal for both front-end preamplification and A/D-D/A conversion. 
 
Best-in-Class I/O 
ProFire 610 features greater connectivity than any other interface in its class. Four unique analog inputs, eight analog outputs and stereo digital S/PDIF combine to form an impressive 6-in/10-out channel configuration. Easily access analog channels 1 and 2 via XLR/TS combo jacks on the front panel. Connect line-level instruments and effects processors to analog channels 3 and 4 via TRS. Use the eight 1/4" TRS balanced line outputs and digital S/PDIF to monitor and interface with outboard gear. Connect keyboards and outboard MIDI hardware to the 1 x 1 MIDI interface. The two front-panel headphone jacks are sourced separately with independent level controls for additional cue mixing flexibility. ProFire 610 allows you to enjoy full 24-bit/192kHz operation on all inputs and outputs simultaneously. 
 
Professional-Quality Design--To Go 
Once upon a time, choosing a mobile recording interface meant sacrificing some of the features and quality found in big-budget studio equipment. Now ProFire 610 changes the game by delivering the same advanced technology and design elements found in our acclaimed ProFire 2626 recording interface. Harness the power of award-winning Octane preamp technology, DSP mixing and 24-bit/192kHz audio resolution in a bus-powered unit perfect for recording on the go. 
 
Features 
•	Up to 24-bit/192kHz for high-definition audio 
•	Flexible onboard DSP mixer 
•	2 preamps with award-winning M-Audio Octane™ technology 
o	Phantom Power

title: Custom gaming, super price
description:
LAST WEEK!!  - Keep in mind you're getting a $300+ new video card, a FAST $185 cpu and a great motherboard at $135 all of which have virtually no use.  PLUS the RAM, CASE, FANS, HARD DRIVE, and WIN 7 PRO all unused until now. THAT'S over $1k in parts/software that we'll donate for the tax break.  Either way it's gone by Friday, Jan 20.  The price is not negotiable.  I have about 12 computers that I need to move to make space for new builds (I can barely walk around the test bench!!) This is the first one I've used Craigslist for (usually Amazon) because we're more than taking a hit on every one of these.  READ the specs, compare oranges to oranges ( I DON"T do "Apple" anything :-)  )  I won't answer questions about specs except to compare.  I've been building over 30 years now and STILL learn something new daily!  This is the best "entry" level gamer with Intel that's out there. 
Intel i5 4460 - 16GB 1600Ghz G. Skill Ram (9-9-9-24) - Asus Z97-A motherboard - EVGA GTX 970 video card (new, right out of the box) - LG DVD R/W drive - 1 Tb Western Digital Blue 7200 rpm HDD - 6 120mm fans (but it's extremely quiet), 3 are red LED - Windows 7 Pro installed - all video drivers installed -  
   This is built for gamers, which means it WILL do everything else, too.  It's also built for expansion, like all my machines for clients.  The board will take any Intel Core processor up to i7 4790K. The MOUSE, KEYBOARD and MONITOR are NOT included, as those are personal preference. If you use WiFi you need an adapter. I will support any issues you come across.  If you break it I'll fix it for you, you paying my cost only.  If we caused an issue we'll fix it at no cost.  But seriously, it's been bench tested and burned in long enough that I wouldn't turn it loose not knowing it was great.  I'll take cash, check or credit card with I.D., make sure you see it running, and let you go feeling comfortable with buying it.  I'll check my email at least 2x daily as the builds/rebuilds allow.  If you don't like this one, keep an eye out...there are more coming, big and small!  And if you're a student at Grand Canyon University carrying your student i.d., then I'll take 15% off...it's my alma mater, too. 
     Any doubters?  Last photo is mine, BigBlue, just a few minutes after posting 24th in the world rankings on Catzilla out of 4k+ entries, and done without liquid nitrogen or helium! Kevin, NoJökComputers.

title: 20 Channel Stage Snake - 100ft
description:
I've got a 20 channel stage snake for sale. It's got 16 XLR channels and 4 1/4in channels.

title: 2009 Yamaha YZ250F
description:
2009 Yamaha YZ250F.  Excellent condition.  Only reason for selling is my riding partner (daughter) moved away for school.  This is a strong running bike. Motor is all stock with the exception on the Pro Circuit Ti Exhaust.  Has AVS break-a-way levers, new rear dirt tire. 
I bought the bike in Pennsylvania without a title.  I've gone through my insurance company and through 2 months of waiting and $100, I have a bonded title: 
What does it mean to have a bonded title? 
A bonded title (also known as a lost title bond) is a certificate verifying a person's ownership of a motor vehicle. A bonded title serves as proof of ownership that allows the owner to proceed with transactions like: Buying insurance. Registering the vehicle. Selling the vehicle. 
Just haven't taking the time to go to the DMV to have it registered and titled.  My reasons, it cost me $30 a year to ride at the dunes a couple times and the tracks charge you whether you have a registration or not. 
 
Any questions feel free to ask

title: Kessler Crane K-Flex Dolly kit
description:
I have for sale is the Kessler Crane K-Flex Dolly complete kit.  Only used once and it's in excellent condition.  Reason for selling this because I'm upgrading to other gears. 
 
Product Description: 
The Kessler K-Flex Dolly Track System is an extremely portable, seamless, flexible dolly track system. The K-Flex Track is a solid, rigid cord, but still very flexible and can be configured in a straight run, or curved in almost any radius or direction (as tight as a 9" radius). This track can be used with any dolly system designed for flexible track with a track diameter of 1-1/4" or with the K-Pod tripod system with Idler Arm and Track Dolly Trucks. 
 
Portable and Durable  
No need to be cautious around this piece of gear, throw it in your gear box or bag and hit the road. Its highly durable rubber material will withstand most any abuse.  
 
Incredible Weight Capacity  
A full-size dolly solution, the K-Flex Track has a weight capacity of 300lbs.  
 
Expandable  
Each 50' roll can be looped to create a 22' run or paired with a second roll for a continuous run of 50'  
 
Lifetime Warranty  
Backed by Kessler Crane manufacturer's Lifetime Warranty. 
 
Items include: 
(1) K-Pod Tripod 
(1) K-Pod Premium Dolly Trucks 
(1) K-pod Push/Pull Handle 
(1) K-Pod Seat/LowBoy Mount 
(1) K-Flex Track (50 feet length) 
(1) Idler Arm  
(1) K-Pod 100mm Ball Relocator 
(1) K-pod Soft Case 
(1) K-Flex Soft Case 
 
http://store.kesslercrane.com/products/camera-sliders/k-flex-dolly-pro-kit.html 
 
http://store.kesslercrane.com/products/mounting-grip/100mm-ball-relocator-ac1001.html 
 
 
I bought this kit brand new for a little over $2,000.  Letting this go for $1,200. 
Locals and cash only.  I will not ship this out of states.  Thank you!

title: Wren and Cuff Pickle Pie B CME w/Mod Fuzz Distortion
description:
Brand new in box Wren and Cuff Pickle Pie B CME w/Mod Fuzz Distortion Pedal for guitar or bass. Boutique ish pedal based on a way huge swollen pickle. 
 
 
 
What is the mod? We call this the "Deep Mod". 
 
The Pickle Pie B was made with a very subtle mid "scoop" in order to let the bass punch through the mix. This is one of the characteristics that differentiates the Pickle Pie B from other muffs. . . More mids! Just for fun, when making the special edition Pickle for Chicago Music, we added a toggle switch that allows you to drop the mid-scoop into a more traditional vintage-style range. One setting is the stock Pickle B, hit the switch, and the notch in the mid-range gets deeper. 
 
This simply makes an incredibly versatile pedal, even more versatile. 
 
Pro Tip: Try the Pickle on regular guitar (especially with the Deep-Mod). With a subtle amount of clean tone mixed in, you'll get the creamy muff sound, with the presence and pick-attack of the unaffected guitar. Great for leads! 
 
 
For a long time now I'd been planning on making a fuzz pedal designed for the many distortion loving bass players out there. It all started when I began getting a large percentage of my Pickle Pie sales from bass players who knew The Pickle's reputation as a "guitar" pedal that could handle the low frequencies of the bass, and give a nice spongy fuzz much better than most of the Muff family. 
 
Even though most were happy with this pedal, I had always wanted to take a stab at doing some tweaks to The Pickle to create a pedal with a much different voice, but one that still uses the same basic skeleton as the PP, and strives to resolve many of the common quandaries bassists come across in their search for a fuzz that really works for their instrument and their playing situation. Long story short, I spent much of my spare time for a few months trying many, many different ideas and experiments till I came up with something I was really happy with. 
 
 
A FET buffered active clean-boost. 
 
No "drop out" when you kick on the fuzz when playing live. Helps give the feel of running two amps, one wet, one dry for those of us who can't afford two SVT's, and/or can't lug two bass amps down to the local club. 
 
Totally changed FET-hybrid clip sections. 
 
Along with great sounding fuzz, this specific clipping combo helps the fuzz to mesh with the clean signal in a natural way, instead of just sitting on top of the dry signal like some fuzzers with clean blends can do. 
 
Altered tone-stack range geared specifically for bass. 
 
A widened range of usable tones from the "shape" knob. The pedal overall has a much less pronounced mid-scoop which helps it to retain presence in a live playing situation. 
 
Altered saturation (fuzz) knob to make it highly usable at lower gain settings. 
 
Roll the fuzz back, and things still sound crisp, also tighter lows at high fuzz settings. I know everyone says this, but The PP "B" really can go from a dirty, gritty, slightly over-driven clean-blended bass sound, to fully saturated, watch out for feedback, drop-C meltdown, and everything in-between. 
 
Various cap and resistor changes. 
 
Several core changes to the circuit to even better accommodate the bass guitar.

title: 1999 Toyota Camry
description:
'99 Toyota Camry with 241,000 Miles. Minor mechanical problems but still running great. $1,250 obo. 
KBB: https://www.kbb.com/toyota/camry/1999/ce-sedan-4d/?vehicleid=6048&intent=trade-in-sell&mileage=241000&pricetype=private-party&condition=fair 
 
Interior is well maintained as you can see from the pictures. Oil changes have been kept up to date the entire life of the car (it's been a hand-me-down in my family since it was bought new). 
 
I'm being totally upfront with all of the issues with the car so you know exactly what you're getting. 
 
There is an oil leak somewhere down under the timing belt. I've had two separate mechanics tell me there's a gasket leaking somewhere under there that is a cheap fix but the labor to get to it would be too expensive for what the car is worth. If you can do the labor yourself or know someone who can do it cheap it will be a cheap fix for a car that's still running great. Over the past few weeks I've just been putting oil in it every couple times I drive and the leak is slow enough that the level stays good. 
 
The speed sensor will throw a check engine code occasionally when it's really hot during these AZ summers. Right after starting up if you don't let it run for a bit and take off driving the engine will rev a little high (just enough to throw the code) and then drive perfectly fine. The check engine light goes out on it's own after driving it a couple more times. Not a problem right now but you'll probably run into it over the summer. I always had o'reilly's or similar store do a check engine code pull (for free) to make sure it was the speed sensor and not something else. 
 
There's some damage to the driver's side front on the light (see picture) but the lights still work just fine. 
 
Paint is suffering from peeling because of the crazy arizona sun (see pic). 
 
To the best of my knowledge this is everything wrong with the car. 
 
 
Now on to what I've had done recently with the car. 
 
About 3 years ago there was a new transmission put in. 
About 2 years ago I had a new radiator put in, as well as new brakes, timing belt, water pump, and all seals under the timing belt. I also had new tires put on that have warranty with them through Big'O'Tire so if they go flat or have any damage you pay a pro-rated fee for replacement (they're a little under halfway through the tread). 
 
Within the last two years there haven't been many mechanical problems with the car other than the more recently developed oil leak. If I knew how to fix it myself I'd be keeping it. 
 
Asking 1,250 obo because the car is still running great but will need a bit of mechanical work. This is a great commuter car! Feel free to email with questions about the car.

It's silky soft with all graphics blended into the fabric so you won't have any peeling, cracking, or fading. The KLEW brand is the same company that make the pro & college ugly Christmas sweaters that are so popular. 
 
This particular Reds polo has the Cincinnati Skyline at the bottom of the shirt wrapping around front to back. inside the body of the shirt is subtle view of the old Crosley Field. The great large iconic Reds C on the front and Team name across the back shoulder. Its a quality made polo that you can get away with wearing to business casual environments.  
 
These shirts retail for $60.00. I am selling this one for only $30.00 brand new with tags. You will notice the packaging is labeled a size XXL, but the shirt is labeled XL. They sent the wrong size and I just don't want the hassle of returning it. Add to that this line of polos runs almost a size small and what you have essentially is size L polo. So that's why I am selling it because it doesn't fit me. Hurry Reds fans and get this stylish polo.

title: Apple iPad Air 64GB A1475 with Lifeproof Case
description:
Up for sale is my iPad Air with the following specs: 
 
Model A1475 
64GB 
Wifi + Cellular 
Space Grey 
LifeProof Nuud Case with Cover/Stand 
 
This iPad lived in it's LifeProof case the entire time I owned it, so it is in great condition and has no nicks, scratches or anything wrong with it. I recently upgrade to the iPad Pro for the pencil functionality, so this one needs to go. 
 
I don't have the original charging cord, hence the orange lighting cable in the box, but it works fine. Everything else is as it was in the package, including the plastic wrap over the iPad itself, so it presents itself as almost new, in the box. 
 
The LifeProof case I am including is the Nuud model and has the add-on screen cover/stand with it. This case and cover/stand alone was around $150. 
 
I was using Verizon but removed the SIM card so you'll have to get a new SIM card to set it up on a cell network. I believe Verizon will give you one for free, but I am not sure about other carriers. 
 
Thanks for looking and please let me know if you have any questions or if you need more info.

title: 2001 Historic 57 Les Paul Custom Black Beauty
description: OK here's a total rock monster. This is a 2001 Gibson R7 Historic 3 Pickup Black Beauty that is in fantastic condition. Non weight relieved all mahogany (no maple top here) body with long tenon neck and ebony board and weighing 10 lbs she has sustain for days! The 57 classics sound incredible. Switching is down position = Bridge pickup, middle position is bridge and middle pickup and up is the neck pickup, the Gold hardware is in great shape As you probably know the R7s are tone monsters and 2001 R7s are some of the best. The guitar will go from clean and classy to rock monster at will. Very low action and fantastic playability, no issues period. The guitar was pro owned and maintained and is in fantastic condition, one small paint chip on the guitar that I have pictured and some very light worming and modest playwear. Comes with case. The 2000-2003 reissues are some of the best reissues ever done. Please no low ballers!

title: 2015 BMW S1000R - MINT
description:
Up for sale is my 2015 BMW S1000R. Only selling because I'm looking for something different. I bought this brand new at GoAZ Scottsdale a year and a half ago. Currently has 4,332 miles on it and I've averaged 40 MPG. I keep it in a garage at home, under covered parking when I (occasionally) take it to work. Bike has the package with quick shifter (no clutch needed for upshifts) and factory cruise control and heated grips. Multiple riding modes: Rain, Road, Dynamic, Dynamic Pro. Electronic suspension: Soft, Normal, Hard, also can specify single or two riders for each suspension setting.  
 
This bike is spotless, I wipe it off after every ride. Oil changed at dealer for 1st service and changed one time after that as well. I have the documentation to go with that. Only modification is a nice radiator guard to protect the radiator and oil cooler. I just took new pictures today Jan 2, 2017 2:15 PM. 
 
This bike was over $17k (after tax, title, fees) at the dealer, no tax when buying private party! 
 
Please only serious offers. I do have a lein on it though BMW Financial so we can meet at your bank to get it paid off and transferred to your name. I will not take payments, and I do not need help selling. 
 
Thanks, 
Mike

title: Brand New Line 6 Pocket Pod.
description:
Hi there, 
 
I bought this pocket pod not too long ago. Soon after I got it though I was able to buy a few guitar pedals for myself. I am a medical student and need the money. Since I have my pedals, I figured I would sell this since I have not used it and do not see myself using it. 
 
It is amazing what you get in this little box. It can be used to play live and can be used for practicing any place that you are, great for recording etc and so ridiculously portable. The tones on it are actually amazing plus you can edit them to fit whatever sound you want. You can also download other people's preset tones based on artist or style. Lastly you can edit everything on the go or on your computer, which ever one you want. 
 
Thank you. 
 
PS: Here is the description from the line 6 website. 
Pocket POD® exhibits all the celebrated features and pro tone that makes POD a standard in recording studios everywhere. Don't be fooled by the smaller package, Pocket POD is packed with over 300 custom presets dialed in by some of today's hottest rock stars like Maroon 5, P.O.D., 311, Hoobastank and many more. Battery-powered and about the size of a tuner, Pocket POD is completely portable. Use it for effects in front of your amp, or just plug in headphones and practice anywhere, anytime. Connect to any computer via USB, then download the free Vyzex software and "deep dive" into all your tone details to create your own custom tone, or manage your own personal tone library right on your desktop. Or visit CustomTone.com to download any of the 3,000 free presets created by guitarists from around the world. Pocket POD lets you sound like a rock star wherever you go.

title: 2004 USA Dean HardTail Pro Mahogany Cherry Burst w/ OHSC
description:
This is an astonishing guitar. It has a beautiful satin finished cherry-burst body and plays like a PRS. The set neck has an amazing feel to it and the pickups have a rich, soulful sound to them. If you are familiar with this guitar, you know they are rare and only come up for sale every once in awhile. These guitars have an amazing build quality and have the playability of a PRS with the sound of a Les Paul.  
 
As far as specs go, the guitar has a mahogany body with a mahogany set neck. The fretboard is a beautiful Pau Ferro which is accented by abalone dot inlays with a HardTail emblem on the 12th fret. It has two volume and 2 tone controls along with a 3 way switch. The Grover tuners, Tonepros bridge, Seymour Duncan pickups, and knobs all have a unique brushed nickel hardware.  
 
This is a genuine, USA made Custom Shop Dean HardTail Pro in amazing condition. If you have never played one or have never considered a higher end Dean, you have to give this guitar a try. It blew me away when I first saw/played it and I believe that will resonate to the new owner as well. Sale will include the OHSC (original hard shell case). 
 
$1200 and open to trades as well. 
 
 
 
Trades Welcome 
 
 
Keywords: FS/FT WTT Trade Gibson American Prestige
